\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid15536214 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Could you tell me whether your father ever mended shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no. My father wasn't a domesticated so
rt of man at all. His interests were entirely on his business. Not his interests, entirely, I mean his time was all spent on his business. He wouldn't know a thing about the house. My sister was being married and she was describing the little houses they'
d
 seen, you know and of course, we used to have coppers for the washing day, you know, with a fire underneath to boil all the clothes, everybody had a copper. And we were saying ... talking about where the copper was, and my father said, 'I suppose we have
 a copper. Where is it?' (laughter) And it was only a small house, you know. He didn't know a thing. His only interest was he liked heat, he liked fires, always, everybody to be warm. And light, he must have plenty of light, and he would go pas}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2914\charrsid8413823 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  the kitchen
 door and say, 'that's very poor light that girl's got in there', you know. Of course, the girls always sat in the kitchen in their spare time. That seems strange to us now, doesn't it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So he was concerned about the light?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. And he would have
 starved if nobody had been there to get him food. Quite helpless about those sort of things. He'd never had to be interested in it, you see. Reading in his spare time, he was a great reader.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did he ever read aloud to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. No, he didn't bother with our reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I wanted also to ask you what was on the first tape recorder: if you could describe to me the first home you had. Was that the one that was behind the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. I was born in the little room above and behind the shop. Very small.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you remember roughly how old you were when you moved from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, we really didn't ... Well, we only moved to the back of it. I can't remember that, but I can remember when we lived in the house at the back playing in the room be
hind the shop, you see. You see, my father had an idea that he could take this little house which backed up to this other one and have covered over a roof, a glass roof, over the two yards of these houses, you see and that made a room, because he wanted t
o start a wholesale news agency, you know, and that was done in there. And, of course, it was a grand place for we children to play in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So you didn't really move out of the house, then? to get the wholesale news agency?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, no. Yes, into this l
ittle house behind. It was only stepping, you know, into the house behind, but that was in a short street which was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 cul-de}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
-sac.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But you did actually move out of that first house? Into the other one that was behind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, but it was all connected to the shop by this glassed-over roof, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I see, so you really expanded your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Expanded, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And kept the original place?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, for the business only.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I see, I was a bit muddled about that. And then when you were about 9, is that right, you moved to a house in Beverley Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, in the suburbs, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And from that house you moved once more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, to a private house higher up the Beverley Road and on the way to Beverley. A nicer house and a nicer garde
n, you know, and my mother and father lived there 'till they died.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And you were married from that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
From that house, yes. No, I was married from the one before. We moved out to the suburbs to a shop and lived in a house above and behind the
 shop, and then we moved just a few doors up the road to a house ... a private house. It was in a row of houses called Ermington Villas. It was a nice house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So Ermington Villas, the family moved there after your marriage, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I was married from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were married from Ermington Villas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Had you lived there several years before your marriage? You were married in 1910. Had you lived there quite a few years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Let's see, I was then 28 and we'd lived at the sho
p 'till ... Oh, yes, we lived some years in Ermington Villas. I should think 10, or more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember why the family made these moves? It was to do with your father's work, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, as a matter of fact he could ... Yes, as first wher
e we lived, it was to do with my father's work. And then he wanted a nicer place for the family, of course, so he took this shop in the suburbs. Very pleasant, all fields behind us, it was lovely. And then, so that my mother should be away from the busine
ss altogether, took this ... went to Ermington Villas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Why did he want her to be away from the business, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, it's pleasanter to be in a private house, isn't it, rather than be mixed up with business. She wasn't then doing anything
 in it and it's a nicer house, nicer living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Your father was from Hull, wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He was born and bred in Hull?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, he was born and bred in Hull, of seafaring people and I think that's why my family are all sailing mad, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you tell me a little bit about how he was apprenticed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, you see, his father died, he was drowned, when he was 4 and so, of course, the mother ... she married again. And that husband died very soon and she had 5 of his children. With 
my father that was 6 and, you see, no widows' pensions, no help with children's allowances, or anything. I don't really know how she managed, she must have been wonderful. And he went to work when he was nine. I don't know what he did, just odd things. Bu
t
 then he was apprenticed, she managed to get him apprenticed to printing when he was ... oh, it would be 14, I should think, and before he was 21 he was a foreman there. And when he was 21 he bought his mother a present with the first man's money he earne
d a brooch. And she gave it to me when I was 21 and I've given it to Sue, when he was 21. She values that very much. Of course, he wouldn't get any presents, you know, they didn't ... children weren't so indulged as they are now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And then later on did he start his own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, he was 24 when he got this little shop, the one where I was born. That must have been ... yes, he wasn't married, my mother was ...

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Twenty-seven I think you said he was married at.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He was married at 27, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And then he stayed in that business. That was his life's work after that wasn't it, running the business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, he started a printing business after that and it got to be, oh, quite an extensive printing business. And my brother, my eldest broth
er, went into the business and carried it in. And he also started, well he got half a dozen retail shops as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So he did awfully well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He did very well. But he wasn't merely a money-maker, you know, it was really interesting business. The sam
e with my husband. It was more an interest in business ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Than just getting money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Than just getting money, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you say to me, too, before that his mother had had a secondhand furniture business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When she had these 5 children sh
e had, and she got a house where there was a paving in the front of this. It was a little above the ordinary path, and I suppose they would put the furniture there, you see. And my father used to when he got home in the evenings, be busy taking all this f
urniture in and everything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that what he was doing when he was 9, do you think? Or do you think he was doing other things as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I should think he'd always be helping her, you may be sure, when he was 9, in all kinds of ways. But 
he didn't seem to think he'd had a hard life. I've never heard him say anything like that, but he didn't think that work hurt anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 A good philosophy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, it was. He really had very good philosophy in most things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And your mother, I think you said, also came from Hull? She was born there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, she was born in Hull.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Had she any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. She was the youngest of all, and the other sisters they all did as well as was usual in those times. You either 
had to be teaching, or ... what else was it? Trying to be a governess or be in domestic work of some kind. And they were all in what you'd call better class service, you know. I know one aunt was ... eeh, I'm getting into the wrong family, but they were b
o
th the same, my husband's family and these similar in station, you see. And aunt there was a stillroom maid - one of Arthur's aunts - a stillroom maid to the Duke of Richmond; and they would be housemaids, or something like that, in big families, you know
, aristocratic families.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She wasn't in service herself, your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, not at all. She didn't do anything but stay home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She didn't work in a shop or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, but just for interest, I think, she used to help Father when she could, in our younger days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But not before marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, she didn't, she did nothing before she was married. She stayed at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And then she used to help in the shop, for a while, after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I think when needed. I think she was mostly looking after the children, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She had enough there, didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, but we always had a little help in the house, living in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You had somebody living in. Could you tell me a little bit about on
e particular one that you can remember, and what he duties were, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, we had several ones. They were all the same, almost one of the family, you know and the only difference was that they had their meals in the kitchen. Well, I t
hink that was merely because they could be ... have it when they'd finished helping with the meal and could have theirs in peace, you see. I think that was all. We had one girl called Chrissie and she came to us because their home was being broken up and 
t
he brothers didn't want to keep it on. And she had intended being a teacher but, of course, with no home she couldn't do that and so somebody recommended her to come to us and she was with us 6 years, I think. And then a relative offered her a post as hou
s
ekeeper, his wife had died, and she went there, but she didn't like it. And then she thought she would rather like to specialise in cooking. She went to some Jewish people and cooked for them and she learnt a lot in cooking and was very comfortable with t
hem. And then she said she wanted a home again, could she come back. And she was with us 15 years, after all, in all, and then she married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When she came back to you, was that after you'd left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, she was there when I was married. Oh, ha
d I left school when she came back? Yes, I expect I had, because I can remember one or two we had in between.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Now, thinking about her, for example, or any of the others, did they have a room to themselves? To sleep in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. But wait a minute; d
id Chrissie sleep in my room at one time? I think there were times when a child or children were in their room. No, I had my sister, always. We shared a room. No, I'd say they always had a room to themselves. Generally the top rooms were where the younger
 children and the maid slept, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And when she wasn't working where did she sit? Or spend her spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, usually in the kitchen, when they were not out, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You called her Chrissie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And what did she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, just by our Christian names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 'Mrs.'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And your mother called her Chrissie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you feel that she as a maid was interested in you as a person? You were a person to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes. In all our aff
airs of course she was interested, and we in hers. She was a member of a choir, a Baptist church choir and they had very good outings, a whole long day in the summer, and they'd go quite far afield, you know. And I remember getting up at 5 one day to do C
h
rissie's hair for her to go on the outing, because they wore their hair then back and in little sausage rolls, just little rolls. A bunch of rolls at the back and she couldn't do it herself, you see, and I remember I had to do ... Oh, and also, I was 13 .
.
. Let me see, she must have come back to us ... Perhaps that's before she went, but there was a young man that she was very sweet on and it wasn't suitable, really, at all, he wasn't ... Well, he hadn't as much brain as she had; and she didn't like to wri
t
e to him. She started telling me, of course, all about it and she didn't like to write to him and, really, put him off. So I said 'shall I do it for you?' and she said, 'yes'. (laughter) I wrote what I thought was a very diplomatic letter and she was quit
e satisfied with that. I think that did settle it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So you were really close to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, we were. And when I married she said, 'I'm going to buy you the best afternoon cloth I can buy', and she did. She went to a nice needlework shop in the t
own and bought me a very best cloth. And she got a girl who was a cripple who did crochet work to do her very best pattern on this cloth, and gave it to me for a wedding present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember about the time off that she and other maids you had were allowed in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Only one evening a week. Yes, one evening a week, from about 6 'till 10. And Sundays ... well, I think my mother was more lavish than most. They used to go every Sunday afternoon and evening. Some didn't have every Sunday afternoon, but ours did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she take an interest in what they did when they went out and when they returned, or didn't she bother about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I don't suppose Mother would ask any details, but if it was anything much, particular they'd been d
oing they'd come in and tell you. Oh, yes, we were always interested, you see, in their affairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
But if one had come in late; do you remember ever an occasion if a girl came back much later than the agreed time, if anything would have been said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't remember. Not if it was ... unless it was very much later I don't suppose. They weren't strict like that in our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you say that your mother felt some responsibility for the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, yes. Yes, she would. Oh, certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you say that she ever game them any sort of moral guidance about how to live and how not to live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, I think she would if they were consulting her, but usually they had the same ideas as we had. But my mother was away and my cousin wa
s staying with us and we thought we would get a maid before she came back, save her the trouble, you see, because we were carrying on in the meantime. And we chose a bright country girl, as we thought, and when Mother came back ... we'd got this girl inst
alled. When Mother came back she didn't like her, she didn't like her very much and she turned out, really ... she was glad when we got rid of her. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 
She was a country girl, but they were very loose in their sexual behaviour. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And she went to a single lady tha
t we knew, and she didn't appear at the usual time. She was not down in the morning at her usual time and this single lady went upstairs to see why she wasn't down and she said, 'well, look in that trunk'. A baby in the trunk, and she'd had this baby in t
h
e night. Well, of course, Mother didn't like her because she thought she was too silly round the boys, you see, that kind of thing. And I can remember when one of the boys came into the kitchen ... we had fire stoves then, ovens at the side and a fire, an
d
 there was a pudding boiling in the stoves then, ovens at the side and a fire, and there was a pudding boiling in the stove and she had to take the pudding out. One of the boys came in and she turned round, took this pudding out and slopping all the water
 
out and all the duties. And really, why she left us ... I don't think Mother would have kept her long, she didn't like her... and she was riding a bicycle and she fell off and got housemaid's knee, so she had to leave. Mother was very, very, glad. But min
d you, she was a pleasant girl and hefty for the work but ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not the type?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, she was brainless, really. She was brainless.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you know if your mother ever talked to her about her ways at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, I don't suppose so, she left that 
to her mother. The mother gave a party when she came back. There was a case brought up if this baby was dead or if she'd killed it, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It's a very sad story, really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It's sad. She didn't mind. The mother gave a party. She had a grand party when she came back home. They didn't care a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She'd been put in jail, was she, then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, she wasn't, but she just had ... there was just then enquiry, you see, the Court enquiry. And, of course, everybody knew. At least, people all ... her 
own friends would. Where she lived was just a few miles out of Hull, a little tiny village and, as I say, they had a grand party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Strange, isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It is. Well, it was just a bit of bad luck they would think. Of course, the pill wasn't invented then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In the household did your mother cook, or did the maid cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I think Mother cooked, mostly. Chrissie cooked. She was a very good cook. She did all the cooking. I think if they could do it ... I don't know, I can't remember. I did a bit, of course, when I was ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At home, when I was older. I made all the bread, and we had a sack of flour, 5 stones I think it is, in a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That's an awful lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, well there were 7 in the household; five children ...
 eight in the household, you know, it took some ... And bread was our ... bread and butter were our specialities. It is mine, now. Of course, it took some doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your mother, when you were a child, make any jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, she used to make jams, and ... well the girls and I do, still, if we can.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she ever make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We weren't very strong on pickles at our house, but yes ... what did she do? No, she didn't do much on pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about bottling of fruit and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Bottling hadn't come into fashion then. It was all jamming, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she ever make any wine or beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The family was teetotal, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about any medicines, do you remember her making up any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, I remember what she used to send for cough medicines. It was a pennyworth of so-and-so, two pennyworth of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Ipecacuana}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , we always had Ipecacuanha in it, and ... oh, that was a marvelous cough mixture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She would send for that, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, send to the chemist. But fancy, pennyworth's of things! The whole thing wasn't much. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 And then, of course, we did get on to Owbridge's Lung Tonic and then the Owbridge family lived at Cottingham, which is now an extension of Hull, a village there 
in a beautiful big house, and we happened to get hold of a pharmaceutical list of what they were composed of and what the cost was.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Have you ever seen them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I've taken }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Owbridge's}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It cost 1/3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \super\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 rd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 . then, but cost them a fraction of a penny. That's why I remember the Owbridge's. Very simple remedies. Camphorated oil to rub on chests and things like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She used to give you that, did she, camphorated oil?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you tell me, in the first house in Beverley Road where did you have your meals? Did you have a dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, but there ... the one behind the shop, do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I mean when you first moved out to the suburbs. The first one by the shop, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It had ... I can't remember. It had a nice litt
le sitting room behind the shop and I can't remember whether we had our meals in there or in the kitchen, mostly. A nice kitchen, it was, you know and I think mostly when the children were there ... We may have had it at time in this room behind the shop.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was what you called a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 sitting room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. No, we had a large }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 sitting room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  upstairs, over the shop. A very nice large }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 sitting room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When would you go and sit in there? During the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, not during the day. Sundays,
 of course, and if you were having any party, or anything. And we had a piano there and I practiced my music and everything like that there. And my father had a lift-on billiards table and several of he and his church friends, his chapel friends used to .
.. they had a sort of club together and they met at each other's houses. One near to us, they kept one room for a billiards room, but we couldn't do that. We had this front room upstairs for this billiards table and oh, they had some fine evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So if friends came in, or anything, that was where you would sit and talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And otherwise you ate in the kitchen, but there was this other room? What was the name that you gave to the other room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't remember, now, what we called it. 
I can remember sitting in it. It has French doors going that way out on to the garden and I can remember ... I was 9 and I took my ... Oh, that would be when we moved. I said we moved at 9, didn't I? And I took my little sister, my baby sister - she was 6
 
years younger than me - only 3, or 2 1/2, I took her to my auntie's whilst we moved, you know. And when we came back she sat on the sofa we had there and she said 'I don't like the new house'. She wanted to go back to the old one, she didn't like the new 
... she was rather a sensitive child, you know. And that's all the recollection I have of that room. Isn't that funny? Perhaps we called it 'the back room'. That was it. We should call it the back room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And you occasionally ate in there, or not? Do you remember ever eating in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't remember us eating in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You had a large enough kitchen to eat in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, and pleasant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did people sometimes come and have a meal with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We didn't have many people come to have me
als with us, but I should think we should eat in there. Like Barry and Betty, they've got a very big lounge with the dining table at the end, you know, but it's been so much more convenient for them, they've got in their kitchen they've got one end with a
 seat in the wall, a very nice table, and they take anybody into there, really. If anybody calls, it doesn't matter who they are, and they want to give them a meal they give them it there. But of course, if it's an invited, formal ... well, larger meal.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Now, when you were in that first house, after you moved out, you know, I mean the first one in Beverley Road, can you remember what there was for cooking on? Was it a range, or a gas cooker, or what type of cooking equipment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It was a side oven; an
 open fire, you see, with a side oven. That's where I baked all the bread. Yes, that was all, we had no gas at the time, just that side oven and it cooked beautifully.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you tell me what you used to have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When we were quite littl
e we all had bread and milk. You'd think that was very insufficient nourishment now, wouldn't you? But we all had bread and milk. And my eldest brother kept ... would have his bread and milk 'till he was a man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He liked it so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Anything else that you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't think we had anything else, unless we had asked for bread and butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have anything to drink besides, at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't think so. When we did have drinks, when we were quite little, it was milk and water. Half milk and half hot water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about Sundays, did you ever have anything different on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't think so. But when we were older, of course, we had ... Can't remember. Can't remember a very heavy breakfast. Boiled eggs
 we were fond of, but I can't remember much bacon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Who served breakfast and cooked it when you were a schoolgirl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The girl that we had, because we came down at different times for breakfast, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your mother come down to breakfast, or did she not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, they came down late, both Father and Mother. Father didn't go very early. He liked to read the paper before he went, and my job was to look after them, you see, when they came down.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that when you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But when you were a child who would see that you got your breakfast and get you off to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I think the girl we had did that, mostly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At dinner - did you call your midday meal 'dinner', then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you tell me what sort of things you would have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, we had just the same things as I provided when I was married. Just meat ... we used to have a big joint on Sundays, of beef ... what do they call it now? Something-bone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Aitch Bone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Aitchbone. And
 it was cut differently from the aitchbones in London. There was one bone, but below that all solid meat. Very nice, that was. And we had that for a midday meal and for supper - always a meat supper - and cold on Monday - that was washing day - and stewed
,
 if there was any left, on Tuesday, but if not then we would have something else. Then we had often, a joint of lamb to go on with, or we had ... we were very fond of stewed rabbits. We used to get lovely rabbits there. Stewed rabbits, or fish. Of course 
fish in Hull was very plentiful and fresh because it's a fishing ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Fishing place, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. And we used to have a lot of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 halibut}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , that was nice. And my mother used to get a large middle cut of cod and stuff it, you know. You know, there's the s
kin part, well, stuff it and a thick slice of ham laid over the top. That was lovely. Yes, that was very nice. All those sort of things; well, sausages, sometimes, though sausages would be for tea, you see, if they had high tea which they always did.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You always had high tea as children, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I was just wondering. The younger ones, the 2 younger ones Ruby and Dick, they used to have a tea directly they got home from school and I suppose they didn't have a high tea but I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were very small when you first went to school, do you remember what you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I can't remember. Food never troubled me much. I didn't mind what I ate, it wasn't terribly important.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It sounds lovely food that you had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, lovely food; and always hungry and ready for it, and it was always sufficient and so it didn't trouble me much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you always have a vegetable every day?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, we had vegetables of every kind. And potatoes, plenty of potatoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have a pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And a pudding, yes, all kinds of puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you have a pudding every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, every day a pudding. Milk pudding sometimes, sometimes a suet pudding, you know. And dumplings in stew and all that kind of thing. Ample feeding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Never any shortage of food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, never any shortage, but not what you'd call luxurious, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did Chrissie, or whoever it was, have the same sort of food as the rest of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And at teatime then, you think the older members of the family had a high tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 On Sundays you said you had a meat supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That would be cold joint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, cold beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And what else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, just pickles, or something, bread and butter. Bread and butter was an accompaniment to everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about cheese?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We didn't have very much cheese as far as I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And you were saying about fresh fruit. Do you remember eating fresh fruit as a child, as part of a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, we used to have it between meals, very often. We had stewed fruit a lot, as part of a meal, for high teas, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have supper every day, or just on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We didn't have a meat supper every day, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You had something before you went to bed, or what time would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
We had this high tea, you see, and there would probably be meat with that, or a good meal for when the boys came home, you know, from work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That would be at what time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Six, that's the usual time if you're ask
ed out to tea now, middle class people. You'll find a meaty spread and sweets and everything, and it's about six.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It's the same in Shetland. I think it's true of the North, generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, they must live very much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was your father home for that tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, he stayed at business, always, very late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Even when the shop was there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, well, he wasn't there. He didn't do anything in this shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, he was in some other place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He was at some other place. They had an assistant there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So he would come home later, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 About 8 o'clock, as a rule. And he was very sparing in his food, his meals. He didn't like heavy meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was he ever home for midday dinner in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, but he came late for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So when you were at school did you have dinner with him, or would you have had that earlier?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, we shouldn't have it ... In fact, we had very few of our meals with him, really. But he was very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 amiable}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , fitting in, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you rem
ember him doing anything with you, as children? I know he used to take you for walks, didn't he? But inside the house, do you remember him telling you stories, or putting you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, he never did anything like that. (laughter) That was Mother's job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you tell me a bit about table manners when you were a child. Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, they were not so strict as that. You just had to sit still and keep ... you know, concentrate on your meal and that sort of thin
g, behave quietly and decently at the table, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a particular way, and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, not so particularly as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But they did care how you held it, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We
ll, I don't know ... we naturally held them. But they wouldn't let you put your knife in your mouth or anything like that, you know, but just normal. I think in a way it came natural.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But if you sort of lent forward at the table with your elbows on it, did they not mind that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, they wouldn't let you do that. Oh, no. Well that is not ... I mean when you've a lot of children, plenty of people sitting close together it would be very inconvenient. Besides which, I know Mother would be very par
ticular about elbows on the table and things like that. Just moderately particular they were, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember if you could ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, I should think so. I can't remember. I usually had enough. But I think Mother se
rved it out equally and there wasn't any left. I think she served it all out when she was serving out. We always had enough and I don't remember anybody saying ... She might have said 'there's just a little more' and given us each, but I don't remember an
ybody eagerly wanting more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And when she cooked the food could you choose what you wanted to eat, or were you expected to eat it all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I think there wasn't anything that we objected to, but as we grew older my eldest brother didn't like frie
d things so Mother did, for his sake you know, have his things stewed or boiled, for him. But otherwise, I don't think there was any special ... speciality. I mean, we had a nice assortment, you know, different kind of things and I think everybody liked i
t.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't remember refusing a particular food when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, never. Now, I didn't like suety puddings, so I wasn't ... didn't have to eat them if I didn't like them. But that's the only thing that I can think of. And she said when 
she was a child ... she was sympathetic because when she was a child she couldn't eat dumplings and she was left to eat a suet pudding and she popped it in the dustbin. I suppose she got into awful trouble, of course, but (laughter...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you ever remember, though, leaving food on your plate that you usually liked? You don't remember that happening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
You must have been a very nice child to cook for. And if there was something out of reach on the table, say, like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, you could ask anybody to pass it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When would you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I don't say they were so polite as to ... you know, children pass to each other without being asked (laughter). Well, I think when we'd fini
shed. I can't remember having to sit there for some other reason, but probably we should be sitting talking until the table was cleared, or something like that, you know. Very informal at our house, and easy-going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Could you bring a toy or a book to the table during mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, Mother wouldn't have that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you ever remember having tinned meat, including corned beef as tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. We had corned beef once in a long while. Mother made Shepherd's Pie out of corned beef and it 
was lovely. But that was the only thing we had tinned meat for, but we used to have a tin of salmon occasionally. Tins were not popular at that time. Some people wouldn't eat anything out of a tin, but we did have tinned salmon and Mother loved a tin of l
obster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about tinned vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Never. Oh, ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Sultanas, I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, sultanas, and what else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Dried peas, and lentils?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, not dried peas. They hadn't ... Oh, no, it was peas you had to soak. We weren't very fond of those. Butter beans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was about all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Fresh vegetables, mostly, yes, very few other ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you grow your own at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, we'd only small gardens, we'd no ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Any hens or any ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, it was too tiny for that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you always have the same places at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did Chrissie, or whoever as your maid, did she serve up the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Now, you were saying that she would serve the food up, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And who would actually take it out of the dishes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Mother. Mother would probably serve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about your father, would he carve or serve at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She'd carve, too, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Food was not his department, he didn't care much about food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your mother carve, or did Chrissie, if there was a joint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Mother carved, always. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When Ruby was little did you feed her or did your mother feed her, or did the maid feed her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, feeding ... I was at school at that time. I was at school when she was born, but all the time when I was at home I took care of her. But of course, at midday it was just getting my own meal and back to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Who would give her her food then, do you think, when she was a baby?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, Mother. We weren't handed over to the help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she sit in a high chair, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, she'd sit in a high chair when she was little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she sit at family meals? On Sundays, for example, do you remember if she sat with the family when she was a year or 2 old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, they all did. Yes, they all sat altogether, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you say that your mother was an easy person to talk to and could you describe what sort of a person she was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes. She was quiet, she was very gentle and she was quiet, but she was very easy to talk to. Oh, yes. She was a little dignified, I should say, but not ... no}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823  comment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  about her, not a little bit, and no idea of position or ... what's the word I'm looking for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Putting on airs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not at all, no. And no competition with the Joneses or anything like that. She hadn't any pride like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was she the sort of mother who showed affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, but not so ... between us all ther
e wasn't so much of the cuddling and kissing type of affection, you know, but it was there and we knew it. You could feel it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were a little girl would she have kissed you 'goodnight', or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, we always kissed 'good night'. And 
when I was very small I hadn't been in the habit of kissing my father goodnight and when I grew a bigger girl I thought 'now, I am going to kiss Father good night', and it was ... it took a lot of doing, you know, because he wasn't used to it, but I went 
and kissed him 'good night' and he was ever so pleased, you know. We always kissed after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How old were you then, when you did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, I don't remember. I suppose I'd be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  12 or 13, I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If you did something your parents disapproved of, what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If we did anything they disapproved of we should have quite a serious talking to, you see. That's all. I never remember any punishment.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't remember that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Who would administer the talking-to, would it be your mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
It would be Mother and if that had no effect then she'd say, 'well, I shall have to speak to your father about you'. And that, well, It was only a quiet word or two, but either of the boys, they wouldn't do anyt
hing that would have displeased Father. I never knew them getting into real trouble, never doing anything ... And I think it was mostly because they ... his example and because they wouldn't like, you know, to displease him. My youngest brother was the li
v
eliest one of the family, but he has always thought a great deal of his father, although they would never show it, you know. And when Father died they sent for me from London - he died on a Sunday, my father - and I stayed, of course, a few days until aft
er the funeral. And I went into the room where Father was and I found him kneeling by his side.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I wonder if you would tell me about that newsroom where you used to slip down and have a read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. I should only be about 7, then, and yes, I used t
o slip down there and get hold of any books, any that I liked. Magazines, mostly, you know. There was a Little One's Own, was it called, the children's own? Little One's Own, I think it was. Oh, I loved that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not Little Folks, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, it was different, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And you also used to read other things, didn't you? Can you tell me a bit more about your reading on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I didn't read any really serious reading. I'm sorry now, you know. I don't know that I'm any worse off for it. Bu
t I used to like stories, you know, and there were some Horner's Penn}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  Stories. Have you heard of those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They were very sentimental. Very sentimental sort of love stories, and a bit of religion in them, as well, these books had. I used to sk
ip the religion and the romantic bits and get on with the story (laughter). I didn't care so much for adventurous stories, travel, not so much for travel and things like that but always must be people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And what about on Sundays, what would you read on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I used to be out most of Sundays, but as a child we had some special books that we used to bring out on Sundays. It was a treat, you see. Mother used to keep those for a treat: the very big Bible with the pictures in. Oh, David ... th
e very big giant with the blood gushing out of his forehead where the stone had hit him, you know, and it was marvelous. We loved that. And we also had given us a book of wild animals ... book of animals and when you opened the page it pulled open a page 
and you see, they were behind. The cages stood up and the animals were behind. That was kept for our special Sunday treat, Sunday evening before we went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I think you told me, too, about a little incident that happened once on a Sunday. Something that your mother was displeased about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
It was when we were sitting at Sunday dinner and 3 of us sat on the sofa and there was a cushion at the end of this sofa, you know, and I was sort of half on this cushion. I was sitting slanting, like that, you
 see. And Mother said, 'get off the sofa, Dora', and I said 'I'm not sitting on it'. I was only half ... a little bit on it. And she quite seriously said 'you are sitting on it and that's a lie, you know. Oh, dear, oh, dear'. I cried all the way to Sunday
 
School because I'd been convicted of lying. That was a terrible thing. Those sort of things they were very particular about; lying, and unkindness and jealousy and, of course, dishonesty in taking anything. Oh, yes, my mother taught us ... what is it they
 said? 'It is a sin to steal a pin and much more any larger thing' (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They told you that, did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, that was just ... she didn't impress that bit on us, she told us that, one of the rhymes of her earliest days, you know. Oh, yes, t
hey were very strict about those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember them ever playing games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, I don't. But there were 5 of us, 5 children, and we always could play with each other. We didn't need the parents to play games, but they would provide us with the games, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What sort of games did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, we used to have the usual games, I think, that ... I was wondering when we were very small, I can't ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have cards, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, playing cards, no. Playing cards were wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, because you could gamble with playing cards, you see, or usually gambled with playing cards so we didn't ... Oh, we played ordinary Snap, Family ... what do you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Happy Families?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Happy Families, and all sorts of games like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Those sorts of card games?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 And Ludo and Snakes and Ladders, did you have those sorts of games?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was there anyone in the family who sang? Were you in the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I used to sing. I wasn't in the choir but I did sing. I had singing lessons. I had a contralto voice and I had singing lessons and my friend and I, we used to go along to the old people's homes sometimes, singing Sundays, you know, to the old folks, th
at kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Just the 2 of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, just the 2 of us. We used to sing the hymns, you know, and we used to sing the popular hymns, what they call the hymns. And when we came home Mother said, 'well, what did you sing?', and I said, 'Oh, Mar
y Sang "Oh, Brother, Have You Told", and I sang 'No, Not One, No, Not One". We didn't know that we were doing that, you know (laughter). And we, of course, ... I spent evenings ... they were musical, Father was very musical, and he used to conduct the Sun
day School Anniversary singing and he could conduct a band quite well. And we used to go round there for musical evenings, then we sang, you see. And she played, she was better at playing the piano than I and I used to do the singing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she live near you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When we moved into Ermington Villas they lived there first, 3 doors away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So, of course, we were always together. She was my age, went to the same school, same church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Had you know her before, then? Or did you meet her when you moved to Ermington Villas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I can't remember whether I'd known her before. Yes, they were in Ermington Villas before us, while we lived at the shop so, of course, I knew her then. The shop was only a few doors that way, 3 doors that way from them, Ross St
reet between, and then we moved about 3 doors the other way into Ermington Villas, so we were with them all the time. So, you see, we didn't need ... There were no cinemas. We didn't need any other evening entertainment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you ever remember anybody in the family reading stories aloud, or telling stories? Did you read to Ruby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You didn't read to Ruby, or tell stories to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I should do, I should think, but I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your mother read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, she wa
sn't a great reader. I think she used to read sometimes. Yes, of course, she did, but I can't remember what she read, either. I can see her sitting in her armchair, but I can't remember what she was ... if she was reading.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have a newspaper regularly in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, I suppose so. Yes. Mother used to like the picture papers, you know, the Daily Mirrors and things of that kind. She didn't go in for much serious reading. She didn't follow politics or anything like that, you know. She w
as not highly educated, she was ... mind you, she was naturally refined but she, being the youngest of 11, she was given quite a good education. She was sent to a private school, paid private school, until she was 11.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I think you told me a little bit about going away on holidays? You used to go away on holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 As a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Were there family holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, let me see, now. When did we begin to go on holidays. Yes, I was 7 and we went then because Ruby was born, 
and Dick was born 18 months after ... She'd had this baby 18 months after the first and never been too well and she wasn't really picking up strength. It was 6 weeks after the baby was born. And my aunt came in and she said ... told Father that she though
t
 Mother ought to go away and she said 'now, I'll find somewhere for you to go at Bridlington'. They had my old grandmother, you know, the one that brought up all those children; she was a marvelous woman, she managed to get hold of a little cottage at Bri
d
lington, just outside the town, and my aunt used to take the children there. And she said 'I'll find somewhere for them to go if you'll send her'. So she said 'yes', and she came in on the Saturday to say that she had found this little cottage. It was a c
o
untrywoman and she could take us in as lodgers, and we'd to go on the Monday. And we had a girl called Becky then. She came with us, of course, to the seaside, and she and Mother, they did all the washing and they got everything ready and away we went, on
 the Monday. It was when I was 7. It was a glorious holiday.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, we were awfully adventurous, we did all sorts of things. We had these cousins there, you see, children of this aunt, they were staying there in a little cottage outside the town. Oh, wonderful!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long did you stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I think that time it would be a fortnight, but later on we always had ... we had a month .. Wait a minute; did we have a month, later? I'm mixing the two generations. I'm getting on to ours, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your father come, as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, no, he couldn't leave the business. He never took a holiday, he never wanted to, but he used to come every ... I think the shops used to close one afternoon a week, Thursday, I think. He used to come
 down on Thursdays always. Thursday afternoon for the half day and take us ... we had donkey rides on the sands, and races, used to send us off racing with a threepenny piece, you know, for the prize. And there was one, just one amusement there and that w
as what they called a switchback railway. You know, these... what do they call them now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I know what you mean, a helter-skelter, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And he'd take us on that. And oh! we had lovely days. We were thrilled to bits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But you did go for other holidays after that, did you? Do you remember, or you're not too sure about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, I think we ... We surely kept on. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Going back to Bridlington, or to other places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, mostly Bridlington. I can't remember where we stayed, except at that countrywoman's house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever stay in a boarding house, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I'm thinking. You see, we went back to Bridlington. I took my children ... we took our children back to Bridlington and I'm confused between where we stayed and where they stayed then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But anyway, you had this holiday at Bridlington, as you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. And then, of course, when I was older my friends and I used to go together. No, Filey, we chose. We liked Filey better. We went sev
eral times to Filey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Is that where you stayed when your husband-to-be asked if he could go and stay at another one nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Yes. Of course, that was when I was very much older. I can't remember how often we went ... I think we constantly wen
t to Bridlington because I remember so much about Bridlington. It's now a very towny sort of a place. It wasn't then. Not so crowded, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were a child, do you remember what age you were when you would put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't
 remember. I know Ruby ... I think she was 12, but she was a very sensitive child. I used to always take her to bed, and Mother said 'now, she's old enough to go by herself so you must let her go by herself'. And we had gaslight then, no electricity, and 
w
e used to light it with a taper. And so she went up with this taper to light the gas in this top bedroom, and she was there, calling out when she got there, 'Oh, Dora, Dora'. It was for me she called always, instead of Mother, and I went on up. And in lig
hting this ... she had a fluffy }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 dressing gown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  on and in lighting this taper she'd caught it just on the fluff of the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 dressing gown}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 and it had just flared up. I think she'd done that (a mime) and just stopped it, but she was scared. So, of course, that stopp
ed her putting herself to bed just for a little while. No, I can't remember. I can remember, after I'd had scarlet fever - I was six - and we had a front bedroom and our bedroom just there, and then there were the attic steps, and you had to pass the atti
c
 stairs to go down the stairs to go downstairs, you see. And when I had this scarlet fever I had awful sort of dreams. I would wake up and I would see ghosts, trailing ghosts, all in white, floating, you know. They had the same faces. I knew them, you kno
w
. Every night, almost. And they lived up this attic stairs. And I used to jump up out of my bed and fly downstairs past those attic stairs. Mother kept me down. She never made me go up again 'till she went, you see, but it would be near their time to go t
o
 bed ... 'till they went to bed and then, of course, I was all right. But it was funny, that. But I understood children's feelings after that. It was just this ... the remains of the fever, you know, I suppose. Perhaps I was running a temperature, or some
thing. But it was very real. I knew my own particular ghosts (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you first moved out to the suburbs you shared a room with some of the family, did you, or did you have a room on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 My sister, always. Always with Ruby, 'till I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And how did the others sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
The boys had a room together. Wait a minute, there were 3 boys. Did they have all in the one room? Yes, they did. It was a largish room, you know, and they had their single beds; and Ruby and I; and of course, Mother }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13117750 &}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  Father's and the girl had a room to herself. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Two of those rooms were attic rooms, were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 There would only be one attic room, for Chrissie, at the end. But there were curtains, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What was the procedure about clean clothes when you were a child? When did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Once a week. We always put clean clothes on for Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was clean underclothes, was it, and clean top clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Of course, if necessary you could have changed them more, but generally everything clean on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And what about pinafores? Did you have different pinafores in the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We used to go to school in pinafores at that time. I remember having one with ... they had lace on, you k
now, or embroidery, and my mother used to like a bit of fine lace. And I remember one pinafore, I had, it had some lovely ... I think it was valanced seams put about. She didn't like fluffy things, you know, nor not loud patterns, or anything. It was very
, very fine, but it was nice. Yes, clean pinafores for school! Fancy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Funny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
, wasn't it? But that was when I was younger. When I went to the ... what do they call it? The ....
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 High school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. We didn't have pinafores there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were at the first school would you change your pinafores more than once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, you wouldn't wear a dirty one. I think we should have it practically every day, I should think. You always had to be clean if you wore a pinafore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did the maid do the washing, or was there a washerwoman who did the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
In my memory we always had a washerwoman. But I think when we had Becky, when we lived behind the shop, down there, I think she did the washing. I don't know whether Mother helped her. And
 I've never seen my mother ironing. But she did the washing. And of course, when I grew up and left school, then I helped. The girl and I did the washing. And I don't know if she did the ironing. Mostly, I think, but you know, I would help whenever it was
 necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have anybody ever else living with you in any of your homes? Like another relative, or a lodger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. Nobody. I realise how }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 wise}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  my mother was in her training, you see. It was the most important things that she really insisted on and that she taught us, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were lucky.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, I was very lucky. I had the happiest childhood, you know. And I used to think ... I now think it's really the people in charge of you, your parents, your home life, that is the most importan
t. I used to think that where we lived, you know, this block-ended street, I've been down there to see it since. Well, poor little houses, you know, but there were always nice people living there, but very small. And we thought it was heaven. I thought it
 
was heaven! And we had no water closet. Earth closets outside, and they were in a little passageway that led out to the main street, and we thought we were very wealthy because we had a front way out into this street, a shop way out into another street, a
n
d the back way out into another street. Three streets! Grand house: grand living to be like that, and to have a place where you could play outside, you see. And, of course, no traffic came down this street and even then the law would be 'no playing in the
 
street' for the children. But of course, no policemen ever came down that way, scarcely. Except one came one day. I think I told you this, that came to the door. Oh, the 3 boys were playing ... some boys were playing with my brother in the street at the t
o
p and a policeman came after them and they chased in, chased through the house and out the shop way into quite a different street. And they came to the house and they said to my mother, 'there are some boys in here', and Mother said, 'no, no boys in here'
;
 and they said 'well, we saw them come in'. 'Well, you can come in and look'. There were no boys anywhere there (laughter). She helped them, because they got out the other way. Of course, we thought ... and they all envied us, you see, having a house like
 that, even with no lavatory and no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What do you think the boys had been up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
We had stilts to walk on. Father would always get us anything like that that we wanted, anything athletic, you see. And I could walk ... there were 3 levels, little 
tiny ... where the foot was put, you know, and I could walk at the highest one. And I used to walk down this little passage and I could see over everybody's back yards, down this passage. Oh, wonderful!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You play out, then, outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, play
ed outside but I didn't like the ... there were nice girls round about, but I didn't like the girls, silly things with their dolls and things like that, and saying 'I shan't be friends with you', you know. Silly girls. And I liked to play with the boys be
st. Boys' games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were living there in that cul-de-sac were there any children you remember your mother not liking you to associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I don't think there were any that were nasty. We should call them nasty, you know, if they were 
mean or if they were dishonest, or liars, or anything like that. No, I don't remember any. They were all quite nice children, although poor, you know. Poorish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But well brought up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember when you moved if you missed the old house and the old playmates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, because we moved out to the country, you see, and behind we had the fields and could climb the trees. The boys used to go and do their homework lessons in the trees outside. And, oh, it was lovely for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't know Hull at all, but can you tell me what was the name of the street, or whereabouts ... it was in the center, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It was in the center, getting more towards the ... well, it was really near the center. Now the City Hall is the center, well we w
eren't very far from there, but we were not in the fish dock part. That's called the Hessle Road that way. We were not in the fish dock part but we were nearer the old town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember what the street was called?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, it was called Charles 
Street where we lived, and it is still Charles Street. But they've sold the ... My brother wouldn't sell that shop - the company's finished now, they've sold it - and he wouldn't part with that shop 'till the very last, just for sentimental reasons becaus
e it was Father's first, you see. But it was in a very sort of poorish neighbourhood down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How many rooms did you have there? You say you only had an earth closet, and you didn't have a bathroom, I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. We had a kitchen and a little ... what we called the back room, that was our }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 where we fed, and my mother put over the window ... she had over the window made a little glass ... well, you might say conservatory sticking out of the windowsill, and she grew ferns and ivy roun
d it and made it real pleasant, you know. We thought that was lovely. And then we had the front room which was the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 sitting room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
, you see, and I had - teaching me that money must be worked for always - a penny a week for dusting that room. A penny. And once
 a little boy friend of mine sent me a lovely Valentine, you know, all lacey and hearts and things, and in the corner it said 'Meet me in Read Street', this was the street at the top of the cul-de-sac, at 11 o'clock, or something, and Mother said 'well, y
o
u mustn't go out until you've dusted your room, and I don't like you making specially a friend of one boy and calling you his sweetheart and things like that. I don't like that. I like you to be friendly with all alike', you see. (laughter) So I hadn't to
 
... well, I didn't want to, as a matter of fact, to keep on ... But I remember that boy said he'd painted me a text, I think it was, they used to paint some texts then, and would I go with him to fetch it from home and it was quite a way through several s
treets. And there we ran hand in hand through all these streets to fetch this thing he'd painted for me. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 And then I was invited to their party and those sorts of things. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And then that passed away, I wasn't particularly ... well, I mean, those little friends
hips you don't keep up, you know. But years later I heard of him and he wasn't at all the type of boy that I should have liked, and he was saying he'd been a special friend of mine and that sort of thing (laughter)
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How old were you then, when he sent you that valentine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, quite a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, quite a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It was before you moved, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, that was before we moved. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you continue dusting the front room when you moved to Beverley Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Le
t me see. When we moved to Beverley Road, no, I was more busy with school, then. I didn't have anything to do in the house ... not in the house, asked to do anything to help, you see. But of course, when I stayed at home, then I always helped with the was
h
ing, made all the bread ... for the cooking and did any other cooking that was necessary, if I wanted to experiment with anything I could. And I loved experimenting with things. I once wanted to do some decorating. My father had had the room papered with 
r
ather an expensive paper and we wanted to ... distempering had just come in and I wanted him to have this room distempered and he wouldn't, he said no he wasn't going to have it. And I said, 'well, look, if I do it would you buy the materials?' Yes, he wo
u
ld do that, so I got this distemper and distempered the walls, and I also got wall papers with a frieze with a festoon of roses and, of course at the top we should have looked awful these days, you know, but it really was quite charming when it was done. 
B
ut you know, they moved into the front room 'till I did this and I kept them in there a long time, because I'd do a little bit and then my friend would come for me to go out for a bicycle ride and off we went! Really, you know, I should have been better t
rained if I'd worked for somebody else. I should have learnt to work better, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But you were a great help to your mother, weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, I was her companion and help, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And you learnt to be a skilled housewife and that sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, yes, but not ... We weren't so orderly and so ruled to times as really would have been a better training for me, I think. It was the easy, pleasant way they went at our house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Still, you ate well, and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes. My husband's sister came down, before we were married she came down to stay with us, and she said, 'you don't seem to go by time here'. I said, 'no, we go by inclination'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But when you children were younger, presumably you had to keep more to time because of school and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, schools, oh, yes, of course we had to, but this was when we were all grown up, you know. We did have certain times, but we didn't mind if things were delayed a bit, or if you wanted to stay a bit longer out, or away, or anything like that, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Very sensible, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, very sensible. Very happy way of living, really. So as I say, you can't take me for, really, an example, because I do understand that I was exceptionally lucky and happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were saying they didn't talk religion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, well, nobody did in those days. If you were polite ... I mean, if there'd been any necessity but they didn't ... like, impress. You wouldn't think 'oh, we are religious people' or anything like
 that, you know. They were real Christian people and we knew they were, you see. Father didn't attend church ... he attended fairly regularly, but as he got a little deaf, well then, he couldn't hear the sermon and he didn't bother so much. But he was a m
e
mber and he was a great help. We moved from the old town and built a church in the suburbs, that's where our shop was, you see, and we got there ... I think we got there first. Yes, we did because we had to walk 2 miles ... a mile and a half into town to 
c
hurch. And he drew up the financial scheme for the ... raising the money for this building of the new church, and they twice had a very appreciative document from the dean of the church for the wonderful help that he'd been to them. He was what you might 
say one of the backroom boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You used to walk wherever you went, did you, in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, Sundays. Oh, we didn't go ... there were horse trams at the beginning, they were electrified later, but there were horse trams and we never went on a Sunday unless you were ill or old. My mother used to take us out sometimes .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Your parents considered it wrong, did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, yes, I think they did, but we did. We did, ourselves, you see. We got into ... we were brought up that way of thinking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 There were trams running, though, on a Sunday, were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, but they didn't start 'till midday. Things didn't in London ... start till midday. When my twins were born - that was 1913 - we had to get a doctor quickly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I remember you told me this, and had to go on a bicycle?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes. And they didn't run until afternoon, and not much was done on Sundays. There was no sport in the parks on Sundays. And the cinemas wanted to open on Sundays and the church people - a lot of church peo
ple - were very much against it, you see, and I thought ... there was a petition being signed and they had it at our church, and I thought 'well, what are these young people going to do, even if they come to church, between 8 and 10 o'clock. All around th
at neighbourhood there were families living in two rooms, perhaps one, but two rooms were generally the most, and where are the young people to go? Where can they take their friends? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 
And so we started, my husband and I just, like, social ... We started if first in the room of the church, just a bit of a social evening from 8 till 10. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
We had community singing, and my husband got all sorts of people there to talk to them on various things. We had ... He was a member of the Hampstead Borough Council for nearly 
20 years and he got the Mayor's secretary to come and talk about the kind of work she did, you see, there, and all kinds of things. He got quite important people, and yet he got the sweep from next door to the Church to come and tell about his work, and e
v
erything, you know. And have a cup of coffee. And then eventually I think some people thought it was rather a nonsecular thing for Sunday evenings. I don't know. Anyhow, it was convenient, we moved it to our house, you see and they were there. And when I 
meet some of those now they always remember. But I think the war finished that, really. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 
But I mean, we were not so ... well, I think we were a bit more broad minded than some of the church people. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 ... Very enjoyable. And you see, we used to have one outing 
from the Sunday School, one from the Christian Endeavour - these were various things. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 And the churches used to have a very good choir outing. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I remember my ... when we had Chrissie, she was in the church choir, a Baptist Church Choir and, oh, they set off 
very early in the morning. They used to go to more distant places, more well known places, you know. And I remember I got up ... I was only a little girl about 13, I should think ... got up about 5 o'clock to do her hair for her and in those days you had 
it back here and then all in little rolls this way (with mine), you know, rolls like that. A bunch of those rolls pinned at the back. And she hadn't much hair, but I got it into rolls for her to go on the choir outing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were quite friendly with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, of course. Well, we always were, but I mean there were girls that were really nice types, although we had some very poor. Once or twice we had some very poor girls, but they were always happy and comfortable with us. We were democrats. My fathe
r would have been ... we should have been in trouble if he had seen the girl wasn't being treated just the same as the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Like he worried about the lights, that she had enough light to work in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I didn't ask you last week: were they both Hull people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Both were born and bred in Hull, both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You said your mother used to help in the shop in the early days
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That's right, yes, she did. She needed to in the early days. Father needed he
r to help. And then, later on, she continued to because she liked it. She didn't have to ... you didn't have to take the place ... not to serve in the shop, but she used to order the things and take an interest, and especially did she like dressing the wi
ndow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, took a great interest in that. She'd like the newest kind of fitments for the window - it wasn't a terribly big window, you know, but it was well worth looking in. She liked something that people had to stand and pick out 
all the nice little things and all the things ... Especially, there was one part for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 toys. One}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 side were toys and the little children used to come along and look in that window. And she heard some... they belonged to the largest house in the neighbourhood,
 and she heard them looking in the window, they wanted to buy something, and they said 'I've got that, and I've got that, and I've got that. Oh, it is a nuisance if you have everything!'
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did your mother do about the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She made most of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, and she made the beautifully. I can remember people saying to me 'that's a very nice dress. Who made that?' and I said 'my mother'. They said, 'oh, your mother is clever'. But I'll tell you what she did. She went i
nto the town and looked into the window at the most fashionable children's dresses and went home and tried to copy them. She hadn't had any training in sewing, or anything, but she was very good. And also, she made the boys' clothes, as far as she could, 
a
nd they wore more coats then, suits you know, not all jerseys, you wouldn't have worn a jersey for school or anything like that, and I remember we had a friend who was a tailor and she went to him and got him to tell her just exactly how to do things. And
 
she made a little Norfolk suit, just looked as if it was tailor made. She was very clever, but she wasn't anyone who boasted about what she could do and we never thought of her as a terribly clever person, you know. Well, you don't think about your parent
s, do you. It's just Mother, but I think, now, that she really was very clever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about mending, did she mend the clothes or did Chrissie, or whoever it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, Mother did. Oh, no, girls didn't do any sewing. Mother attended to all the cl
othes. And then when I was at home, when I was old enough, I mended the stockings. I did anything of the mending that was necessary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about shoes? Where did your mother get the shoes, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I don't know where we got them, bu
t she would always have good shoes, and fitting shoes. And broad toes were very much in the fashion then and we always had to have nice }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 broad}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 -toed shoes and, you know, the shoes we're wearing now, like you're wearing ... oh, yes, they've gone back to a broad toe, but you get more side ... they're really more comfortable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, broad shoes ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
They were narrow at the ... No, the broad toes were narrow at the sides. And now you get the more pointed, it fits you so. These round toes that have been popular lately are far more natural and comfortable, I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She didn't get them specially made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I believe she had to have her own shoes specially made. Yes, I think she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about mending shoes, how was that done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, you send them to the shoe mender.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember if she ever bought anything in the way of secondhand clothing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She wouldn't have needed to, would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, she didn't need to. And you wouldn't buy ready-made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She wouldn't buy ready-made things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Nobody bought, really, clothes ... except ... well, very poor. Nobody else, as you might say, would buy ready made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If you could afford it, you didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, we had them all made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was there a particular time of the year, or a particular occasion at which you got your new clothes, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, always at Easter time. Or was it Whitsun, or both? I'm not sure, I think it might be Whitsun. That's a little later, isn't it. Oh, yes, you always had new clothes about that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have sort of processions at the church at Whitsun?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, we didn't have anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have any particular jobs that you had to do when you were quite a small girl? I don't mean when you got older, baki
ng bread and that kind of thing, but as a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, Mother liked me to ... Well, I remember when I was 8 years old on Saturday mornings I had one penny for dusting this little front room that we had, the little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 drawing room}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , you know, before I went
 out to play I had to do my work which was dusting this tiny little room that didn't take many minutes. But Father liked us to ... brought up to think that money had to be worked for, you see. But it was very little that was done for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long did you continue doing that? Did you do it after you left school, the front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't think I did any more work, later on. Nothing that I was supposed ... you know, expected to do. Not when I was at school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And what about the brothers and your sister, Ruby, did they do anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. Ruby was a teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I mean when they were small children, did they do any jobs in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't think so. I don't remember. And my job, of course, was looking after the babies because I had 
my younger sister and then the youngest boy who was only 18 months younger than her. I took the management of Ruby over entirely. And the girl that we had was quite capable of doing the work, you see, we didn't need to ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 To do that, no. Do you remem
ber when you were a schoolgirl, and a little girl, you know, say 5, 6, 7, if you had to be in bed at a certain time? Was your mother particular about bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, I think she was. It wouldn't be, perhaps, on the dot of the time but pretty nearly. Th
at's why I should know when bedtime was coming on when I escaped and went to read. When I got away from things and went reading, so that I didn't have to go to bed. But yes, we did go to bed at regular times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she put you to bed, or did somebody put you to bed at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I can't remember her putting me to bed. I must have put myself to bed pretty early. But I put Ruby to bed. Oh, yes. She was rather a nervy child and we had our bedroom on the top floor and so I used to take her. As a matter of fa
ct, when she was a baby she wouldn't go to sleep unless I was lying by her side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How often did you bath in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was in your own bathroom, wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, we didn't have a bathroom at the first little place, but in the bathroom, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And when did you have ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I used to bath ... The boys had a cold bath every morning. This was when we had the bathroom, you see. And I was interested in this health movement that had just come in, you know, at th
e time; didn't wear a stiff corset, only a very light one, and I had cold baths, too, for a time, very bravely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Why did your brothers do it? Was it their own idea, or was it your parents'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It was for health's sake. My brother who died at 83 a little while ago, he always had his cold baths, right 'till the very end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Your mother, was she sympathetic to the health movement, or was she not interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, she wasn't ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She wasn't interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, and she wasn't a very tough type, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was she an easy person to talk to? Did you have chats, cosy chats with her, was she that sort of person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, very easy to talk to. Oh, yes I felt very much at home with her, you know. Oh, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you ever remember telling her any worries you had or any fears about things? You know how children sometimes do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't think I had any fears, much, about anything, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If you had had any worries about anything, would you have kept it to yourself, or would you have gone and told her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You see we'd been taught ... from little children we'd been taught to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 
pray}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, I remember you told me about the thunderstorm and how you prayed then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And then, you see, when I was older ... Well, we'd been taught Christian
 principles, you see, and I think I was about 7 years old we went to the seaside to stay for the first time and there was a children's special service mission - it's still going, I think - and there was a very nice gentleman there who was running this, an
d
 we had the services ... the children all gathered together early and built a great big castle and made it firm, for a pulpit, and a little short text for the day we'd put round in seaweed. And then they dug seats, circular, you know all the way round, an
d we were attending there. Oh, we did like that. And they sang very lively little hymns and things, and I think it was then that I realised that ... well, you had to be a Christian, or you didn't. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were about 7?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. And I thought 'w
ell, I am a Christian and I shall stay so'. Would you call that conversion? I don't think so. I was no such thing, but anyhow ... and so of course, I stayed so. And then, of course, if you'd been ... always got that idea you pray about your worries, and y
ou always feel you've got that background, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
What about your father, did you feel at your ease with him when you were with him? I know he was working very hard and was out a lot, wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes ... Well, you didn't have absolute conversat
ions, only just as you were living ... mealtimes. And then, he didn't have meals very often with us. Midday, but of course, we were at school and he would have his a little later, and we had to be rushed, you know. But yes, I always felt quite easy with h
im.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How did your parents expect you, you children, to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, they wouldn't let you say anything disrespectful or rude about, or to, your parents at all. Well, you didn't expect to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you ever remember doing so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It just didn't occur?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did they think about swearing, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, they wouldn't have swear words, I don't suppose. I don't remember the boys trying to, really, but perhaps they would when they were not at home (
laughter). Archie wouldn't, the elder boy, he would never do anything that he didn't think was right. He was a very nice boy. But }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 Don,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  the monkey one, he would (laughter).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember if your parents brought you up to behave towards your sister and your brothers in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, they wouldn't be ... they wouldn't have any quarrelling. I remember my 2 brothers, they got heated with one another and they almost had a fight when I was there and I was in tears, weeping, and did hope 
Mother would never get to hear of it. She was out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she get to hear of it, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, I don't think so. And she wouldn't have any ... very strong about jealousy between children. There mustn't be any signs of jealousy of any kind. We didn't feel it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was she particular about treating you all the same, herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, absolutely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And if you'd gone to her and said that somebody had hit you or knocked you down in the playground what would she have said about that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, they never did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It didn't ever happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, not in a girls' school, you know. There wasn't any roughness.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you think she would have told you to hit back if anyone had ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no. Oh, no. I don't think so. I've never had reason to ask her opinion on anything of that kind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When grownups were talking, were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, We shouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you be sometimes in a mixed group of grownups and children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not much. Well, we had to be quiet, you know, not much where we were ... where grownups were. We weren't interested.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Would you say that the ideas you had about truthfulness and honesty, and generally the ideas you had about how to behave, that you got them more from your mother or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  from your father, or was it equal do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Equal. Quite equal, yes, they both felt the same about most things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember a birthday when you were a little girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What happened on a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 My birthday was in May, and my mother always managed ... at least, whenever she could ... manage to take us on a picnic. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And do you know, we were in a town and it was ... As I told you, she was very heavy, she was very fat and also she was not very good at walking, I don't think her feet
 were very good but you know, she managed and I think now, how she managed it I don't know. We did a considerable walk to the railway station and then we went one ... one or two stations on the railway line to a little ... very pretty little village near,
 
carrying the picnic tea for all these ... And I don't know how she managed it, really. And she used to take ... There wasn't a tea place of any kind, but there was a cottage ... There was a pond in the ... down below and the houses were higher up. It was 
a
 very picturesque little village, supposed to be. And there was a woman in the top house who would boil your kettle for twopence. And she used to take a kettle, I don't know where we got the water, perhaps she filled it for us, and boiled this kettle and 
m
ade tea. And she must have carried a teapot and mugs, you know for us children. I suppose the boys helped in the carrying, I don't remember that. But oh, that was heaven! There were not many wild flowers round about Hull because it's near the sea and just
 flat, but }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 harebells}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , and if I could find a few }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 harebells}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  on the way, my word, it was lovely!. Yes, that was a beautiful time. And she sent me a little ... she sent me a letter ... what do you call it? Weight, you know. You know those little glass...

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Paper weight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Heavy paperweight, with a view on the bottom, you see, of this very little village. And on my door I've got the knocker of William }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Wilberforce}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , he was a most important man, the man who helped so much in the slave ... freeing the slaves.
 They sent me that. It's a knocker of his monument.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that round those parts, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, he was ...}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Wilberforce}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  House is in Hull.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you went was it just the family, or did you have any little friends going with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, we couldn't take anybody else, there were enough of us. Mother had got enough to take with 5 children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have a special birthday cake, or anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I expect we should have a birthday ... we didn't have cakes very much. We had bread and
 butter, homemade bread and butter which had come straight from the farm, used to come about twice a week, you know. And bread and jam, homemade. But we didn't often have cakes. But Sunday, you know, and special days, oh, yes, we had a birthday cake.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about Christmas, do you remember Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, I remember Christmas. We had fine Christmases, we enjoyed them very much. One thing they did in Hull, you know, your house was almost spring-cleaned for Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Really? How interesting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes. Clean curtains, everything up for Christmas. And for Hull Fair. We had a very big fair, it was one of the biggest in England. It is still, I think. And all the cleaning and everything that was ...and special things people used to make for 
the fair, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That you used to buy there, you mean? You used to buy things at the Fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We used to make ...they called it Brandy Snap, it's not called Brandy Snap now, you know the curled ...crispy...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I know, you fill them with cream or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, yes, but they didn't fill them with anything, and ours were flatter than that. Well, you either made them or they were sold in great quantities at the Fair. Two things were sold; that, and green grapes. Isn't that funny? 
Oh, and you used to have hot peas, cooked, you know, on the stalls. We never had anything like that cooked out of doors. And they had stalls where you could buy things and we, one fair time ... oh, I was quite small, I don't suppose the youngest one was b
o
rn then, but we had a girl called Alice. And Alice - she was a very nice type, she belonged to a very nice family but her mother was left a widow, her father had been a sea captain and the mother was left a widow and she wanted a home for Alice when she g
r
ew up because she, herself, was a housekeeper, and so Alice came to live with us because she was a relative of a relative, a connection somehow, you know. And Alice was just one of us. In fact I remember the girls, the other girls in our street would come
 
and knock at the door and say 'please can Alice come out to play? 'Cos she was very young, only about 15 or so, then. Well, she engineered this, that we should save up our money and at the Fair we should buy Mother a birthday present. That was for October
. The Fair was in October. Well anyhow, we were saving up this money for her and I saved three }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 ha'pence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
. I think I had a penny a week and I saved 3 ha'pence, and the others ... we managed 6 pence ha'penny between us, and Alice minded the money and took us t
o the Fair and we bought a marvelous ... for 6 1/2d then you could buy things, you know ... celery glass, that tall. They used to have a tall glass for celery, and we bought this celery glass. And Alice hid it when we got home and nobody had to say a word
.
 But Don who was the smallest one and used to climb into his mother's bed in the morning sometimes, he would say 'I'm not going to tell you what we bought at the Fair', and then a little bit later ... she told us this afterwards, we thought she was having
 
a grand surprise. And then a little bit later he said, 'I'm not going to tell you about that surprise we've got'. 'I'm not going to tell you that ... it's a glass', and then in the end; 'I'm not going to tell you it's a celery glass (laughter) She told us
 afterwards how bit by bit he'd got it out, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 hat he was going to buy that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But she didn't tell you at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She played the game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She let us have ... And on Sunday mornings when we were small, to keep us in bed a little long
er there was always a little surprise for us on the dressing table in Mother's room, a little sweet or something like that, and a bit of chocolate, or really something nice, you know, and we went back to bed to eat these, and stay quiet a bit longer. At l
ast, after a time, we began to grumble. We said 'oh, is that all? Or something like that, so never again! 'On, well', Mother says, 'it's time we stopped, then, if you're not satisfied, So we stopped.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You never had any more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. We had it another way, I expect, but we never had a ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It was her way of showing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. You must be satisfied with what you have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You think the Fair was in October?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. It was on the 11th October every year. Mind you, it was a monstrous affair, bu
t it was a great affair for the town. It's a big fair now, I think, it is still. But we used to have to walk a long way to get there. But Mother couldn't take us to the fair, whoever we had then, until we were old enough to take ourselves. But the girl us
ed to take us. Not Father, he was in business. He was never free for anything like that. He would have liked it, I think, if he'd been there. Yes, we had fine times.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And on Christmas Day were you just the family together or did you mix with relations and friends on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, we didn't do so much. The relations were all near but we didn't visit much, especially, not on special occasions. We just popped in, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But you did see them on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, some of them.
 Those who were near. But we had a tremendous number of cousins and things, some that I really didn't know and some that ... the parents had lived away and then they'd come back, you know, and we didn't know. But the others ... as I say, we used to pop in
 and we used to drop in on Christmas Day. My father always went to see his mother while she was alive Christmas Day, and any special days, and very, very often on Sundays, be would go down to see her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever go to see her, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, I was t
he visitor for the family. The boys didn't, they didn't visit, but I used to visit when I was at home quite free, you see, to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were small, about 9 or 10 did you go there on your own, or were you taken to see her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Nine or 10?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you'd just moved to Newland, did she live near?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She wasn't too far away. She lived in the street that was off the {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Beverley Road{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and not too far away. I should think I could go when I was 9 years old. As soon as I was old enough, you see, to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Had she moved out there with your family or had she lived there for a time before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, she'd lived there all the time before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she come to see your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, occasionally. But she wasn't a very sociable old lady. We didn't kno
w her very well, but I've known her since ... through cousins of mine. They lived in London and she was very fond of getting up to London if she could, to see them and they know more about her ... Well, that was a little earlier days than I should have kn
own. But she'd been a very clever woman bringing up the family that she did. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 
She had ... my father, of course, his father was drowned and he was only 4 and she married again a very nice man and had 5 more children, then he died and she was left. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And you kno
w what it must have been, with no money, no children's allowance, no widow's allowances, you see, and she managed. She managed, yes, she'd been a very clever woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember a funeral in the family at all when you were a child, or a young girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, not in our house, but I remember my grandfather's funeral. My Grandpa's funeral. I was 8.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, I didn't go to the funeral. They wouldn't have taken a child to the funeral, but one of my aunts, she'd been left a widow and
 she was running a sweet shop, and they left me to mind the sweetshop while the funeral was on. Oh, it was the time of my life! I sold somebody some sweets at a much lower price than they ought to have paid, but that was lovely!(laughter) So I only rememb
er funerals with pleasure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have nothing to do with the actual funeral, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you know if they came back afterwards and had a meal in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, they always did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But you didn't partake of that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. Oh, no. I just stayed in the shop 'till my auntie came back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was there any funeral that you did take a part in, up to the 1918 War, for example?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. No, I don't think I did. You see, we didn't have any children die. No, I don't know much abou
t funerals. But everybody did have ... they always went home, you know, but they used to talk about 'burying him with ham'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But personally you don't remember one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about Bank holidays, were they a feature in your childhood at all? I
 know you used to have a nice two weeks' holiday, but did you have any excursions on Bank holidays, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't think we went away or anything like that, but I always had a hoop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, Easter I always had a hoop
, a big one, as large as I could get because I could run fast, you know, and you had to keep going with it. The girls had wooden sticks and the boys had a little iron stick with a ring to keep on these. They had iron hoops. And Battledore and Shuttlecock,
 yes, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Easter time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , and the boys had marbles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The Battledore and Shuttlecock and hoops, did they start coming into season at Easter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You had sort of seasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, they had seasons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What were the other seasons of games? Do you remember any other games? Did you do hopscotch at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I didn't do hopscotch, that was played on a pavement as a rule, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you not ever play in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Of course, in the little street that was the cul-de-sac we p
layed there, but when we went up to Newland, you see, there were fields all behind and there were buildings going up all around us. And immediately behind our back door was the place where they were sort of ... constructing the things for the buildings an
d
 there was a great big lime kiln with a little wooden fence round it about so high (with mime). And we used to walk around this fence, you know, walking tight-rope, we called it, you know, balancing. I slipped in one day, went up to me ankles in white lim
e
. Oh, my mother did ... I went inside and got everything off, but it didn't burn. Well, it was a lime mixture. We called it lime, it was sort of for cement mixing, you know. Oh, yes, I was a terrible child. My poor mother ... for the clothes, I don't know
 how she managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did your mother say when you fell in the lime kiln?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I don't think ... I don't remember telling her anything. I think I was big enough to go inside and get it all into water and look after myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played? In your general sort of play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, I expect so. I don't remember anybody being ... The little ones that I looked after, you know, when I was older, they didn't get dirty, not very dirty. I don't know how that was but I don't 
remember them getting ... They were bathed daily, of course, when they were older. But I mean, we weren't meant to keep our clothes ... to take much notice of clothes except to be careful, you know, but not for appearances, only for keeping our clothes, y
ou know. Mother wouldn't have liked us to have gone out looking too ragged, or not looking dirty, but wasn't particular about ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she sort of dress you up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, not ... She didn't like dressing up. She would have suitable clothes, good clothes, she liked, but not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did some children that you'd meet, say at church, dress up rather a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, my cousins ... we were very friendly with one family of cousins and their mother had more idea of dressing them up, but then, she couldn't affor
d it so she couldn't do it (laughter) as she would have liked. But I remember when they were small - there were 2 little girls about my age, one was my favourite cousin and her sister - and they were dressed up a little bit more. I remember them having la
rge plush bonnets and all ... you know, show things. Mother didn't like showy things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you have liked that yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, not showy things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You didn't fancy it yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I liked the things Mother liked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You liked good taste?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, of course, I mean, brought up with her, so naturally we would, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When your parents weren't working did they have any sort of leisure activity, anything they used to do together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. Mother couldn't get around very much, you kn
ow, she was too tired, and Father ... Oh, Father ... not together, but he liked playing billiards and we had a lift-on table, not full-length, you know, a little bit smaller, and he and his other friends mostly belonging to the church - I think all of the
m
 were, nearly - they had a sort of informal club amongst themselves and had evenings, and oh, they did enjoy that! My friends that lived ... the brush manufacturer people that lived near us they had a room, a spare room, which they made a billiards room, 
so they had a proper ... a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 full length}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  table. But that was Father's sport, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was he a member of any sort of club or institute of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And your mother, was she at all, besides the Church sewing circle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, mother was a home person. Absolutely home person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did they do anything in the way of local charities or organisations or anything of that sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't think so. Our Sunday School supported a cot at the children's ... We had a very good children's hosp
ital in Hull and ... I was just thinking about any private donations ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I meant really were they members of any sort of organisation which raised money, or that kind of thing, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I think they would help, but they didn't take office with anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They weren't sort of committee people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, no, they weren't people for ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Or in local government?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your father bet at all, or go to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no! Gambling! My dear! Gambling? Terr
ible!! Oh, we were always brought up to think gambling was wrong! Well, it is such a danger, isn't it? It becomes compulsive, yes. I remember Larry, later on ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was your father interested at all in sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, he was interested in sport. He was interested, but I can't remember talking about ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did he go and watch at all, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, football. Oh, yes, a keen watcher of football. Of course, he'd never played, but the boys did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did any of you go with him to watch football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I'd no interest in football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you know if your father or mother belonged to any savings club? Did they pay money into any clubs like a funeral club?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When Father was first starting and they had us as babies, you know, he put a li
ttle insurance in ... well, really, to pay for a funeral if a child died, as they often did then, you know, and it was twopence a week. And do you know, that twopence a week was paid for me for years and years and years, I didn't know it was still going o
n
, but they paid it when they moved when they got an office where the printing works were, you know, and all his accounts were there, and it was paid from there. And then it lapsed for a long time and I thought about ... Oh, and they sent me the books, you
 
know, that they'd finished paying it, or asked me if I wanted to continue it and I said 'no. And so I thought afterwards, well they paid in quite a lot of money over this time and I wrote to them and said was there ... would there be any rebate because of
 the discontinuance. Oh, they said 'yes', they said there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13117750 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
10 if I sent these books up to the ... at least, if somebody sends them when I die (laughter) they'll get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13117750 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 10.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not very much after all those years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not very much, but still, it was wo
rth sending it. But that's the only thing that I know of, but I expect he had an insurance. I don't know, I don't think he had. He shared out his shares, the family, oh before he died, earlier years before, and left Mother with so much a year 'till she di
ed and, I think, lose money. Anyhow, she was well provided for, you know, but there was no insurance. I should have heard about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was there one brother that you felt particularly close to? When you were a child, I mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I don't think. I t
hink my elder brother was ... but he had boy friends and all that kind of thing, but he was the gentler type. We were very friendly, all of us, you know. I realised the difference in them, but he would take me ... For a year after we moved up to the subur
bs we had to go back to our school for the next year's examinations, for nearly a year, and he took me down on the back of his ... He was a very kind brother, that one ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, he took you on his bike, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Very kind, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that back to your church school, that he took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were a child did you play with friends and with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, and with neighbours that were near, round about. Years afterwards a man came, he was a Church minister and he'd been
 one of my closest pals in that place behind where my foot went into the lime. And he came to visit us again and talk about old times, and said he well remembered how I teased him when he had to go into long trousers. You see, they set the age ... }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Knickers}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 'till you were, what? 12 or 14 - about 14, I should thing - then you went at once into long trousers and stayed in. Never knickers any more. We hadn't got the scouts then, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember if there were any children that your parents forbade you or discouraged you from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I was thinking of that the other day. There weren't any, and I think there weren't any that were nasty. I should have known it and Mother would have known by us talking about it if there had been. No, I
 couldn't think that there were any disagreeable children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember ever going to the theatre? You mentioned the Panorama and the circus and fair, what about theatres or concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, we didn't go to theatres.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would they have disapproved of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, theatres. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 
The theatrical profession in those days was not supposed to be ... well, they were what you called 'fast'. They'd be a bit loose living, you know (laughter). }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, we didn't go to theatres, but my father was very fond of 
music and he always went to the ... if any Gilbert and Sullivan opera came, he always went. And I didn't go, he didn't ask me to go with him, but I know he would have loved me to go with him. And because, as I say, I was secretary of the Christian Endeavo
ur Society and you didn't ... it was supposed to be just gaiety, you know, sort of theatre life, I didn't go, and I think now what a little prig I was. He would have enjoyed it ever so much if I'd said 'I'll come with you'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were telling me last wee
k how there was this children's dance for the hospital organised by what you would call the higher class people round there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I'm wondering now if perhaps it was more the cost that kept it to one higher class of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was it quite expensive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, it was rather expensive, I think, but still not too expensive that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 
trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  couldn't have gone if they'd wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And round where you lived you were saying there were mostly white-collar people; in what sort of jobs were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, clerical work, office work, you know, mostly. And teachers, and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Who do you think were considered the most important people in Newland at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't know. There was a canon at the local church, Canon Lambert. When I was young, really, of course, I didn't know much about them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about when you got older? You know, in the years before you got married? You know, when you were grown up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't think who would be the most important. There was a mixture and we accepted ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I'll go on asking you about Newland and what the different social classes were at that time. Could you describe to me how you sort of saw ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It was a mixture. There was nothing particular, I don't think. There were rather larger houses ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, that's what you were saying, there were some quite large.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, but we didn't know those people and I don't remember them having any public positions that I should have known. But then, I wasn't interested, much, in those kind of things.
 We knew the doctors, you know, their names and that sort of thing, but I don't remember other particular people. There was the Rank family, they lived in Hull and they were Methodists. Are they called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Wesleyans}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  now, or Methodists? Methodists. And they use
d to come up as a family to church and we were walking down to our town for church and it was quite an event if we men the Rank family coming up to church.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 There were the flour ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The flour people, yes. And I should think one of them would be the Arthur Rank who was the leader ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, it's the same family, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, it was their family, but I think he would be one of the smaller children, now the cinema one, you know, that came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Who did the doctors mix with socially? Who were their friends, and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about the Canon and clergy, other people, do you know who they mixed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I don't know much about them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were there any teachers that you and your parents mixed with in social life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, we didn't have much of what you would call social life, it was more home life, you know. There wasn't much social life outside, for us. I'm trying to think of the teachers of that time but when I went to the Highgrave School, no
, I didn't know anything about their private lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were a child, were you brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, nothing at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were you ever told to curtsey to anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no. That had gone out before my time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember if your brothers or your father touched their cap to anybody or raised their hat, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 My father would raise his hat, but there was no touching or caps in those days. That had gon
e, or it might have been in the country, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But not where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember calling anybody when you were a small girl 'sir' or 'madam'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, they didn't do that, but the young men ... Well, this wa
s later on. If they respected anybody they would call him 'sir', an old man, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 An older man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, they would call him 'sir', but it was never ... I suppose a servant of some kind might have called the master 'sir'.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was your father called 'sir' by anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, no, not by his employees. 'Mister', probably, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And do you remember anybody calling your mother 'madam'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have anything to do with the Church of England at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. My brothers marrie
d girls who ... we had friends, you know, but nothing to do with them. Our two youngest went to Newland Church School, first little primary, you know, but we didn't know many church members. Our friends were mostly among the chapel people, as it's called.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Would you say there was a different type of person who went to the church from those who went to the chapel, a different social class or anything, in Newland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I think it was generally supposed to be the more conservative ... the people more of t
he Conservative politics, you know, that were church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was it? That's interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In that area were there many poorer people around who had much less money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, nobody really poor in that neighbourhood. It was just a new suburb, 
you see, mostly. There was round in our old house. Talking about the difference in position: my Mother used to send ou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 the collars that were stiffly starched collars to be done. Other washing was done at home but the collars had to be taken constantly, an
d we children would take it. And my elder brother ... there were 2 ways we could go. One was down a nice street that had little gardens in front, the other was down a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 slummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  street. They were parallel. And my brother made me go pulling my hair, holding my hair all the way down this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 slummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  street because he said I was proud. I wanted to go in that better street (laughter) And to be proud was terrible in our family. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 
It was a terrible thing to be proud.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember your parents talking to you about how you should behave to people who were poorer, or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, because they wouldn't expect us to be unkind to anybody. And never to think yourselves better. That was one thing they were very strong about. You mustn't have any conceit at all about yourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Do you remember when you were a young girl a distinction being made between respectable families and rough families at all? Do you remember people talking about that, or being aware of the difference, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. There we
re people that you'd call 'common', people that ... low-class ideas. They would be common, those people, but there wasn't anybody of that type amongst our friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What sort of ideas at that time would have been considered common?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, speech, and rough ... loud behaviour, you know and language, probably. I don't know, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Generally, not being quiet and refined, and that sort of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, generally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember being aware of the distinction between craftsmen and labourers when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You wouldn't have come into contact with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I shouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were brought up not to think of yourselves as proud and special ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But were there families that
 you knew who did sort of put on airs or consider themselves to be better than others, do you remember, that you came into contact with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't think so. We wouldn't have made friends with them if they were that type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't remember people who thought themselves superior to others in that sort of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Your father's attitude you were saying was very democratic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, very, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was your mother the same? Did she have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I don't think we bothered about classes at all, really. Not at all. But my father, as I say, was very democratic and when he was a young boy he had to help his mother when he was working and I think he used to, perhaps ... as I t
old you she took ... well, the stepfather which he had for some years, but he died quite early, he was a carpenter, and I think he used to take round the things he made. You know, my father used to have to be errand boy for him. There was something he had
 
to take round, and he used to a bit about what he took round and I think either the boys teased him or he'd said once he'd taken oranges to sell, and so of course, they teased him very much. And we were going to a new house - not that first move, we moved
 
higher up the road a little later on - and it had a name. Well, most of them had a little name, you know, not big houses, not what you would call a large house but bigger than the other one, and the boys suggested that we call we called it St. Michaels be
c
ause ... is it St. Michaels, the very nice oranges that there were at that time? They would tease him, you know, about things like that. But in the end somebody suggested calling it Caxtonia, the inventor of printing, you see, Caxton. So they did. Called 
it Caxtonia.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were saying that you don't think they were conscious of class? Would you say that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I think they would be conscious of it, but it didn't trouble them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It didn't trouble them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. They weren't ever trying to get into a higher class. Never.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
If somebody had said to your mother, in a social survey or something, what class was she, or what would she call herself what do you think she would have said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't know whether she would have known, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Or don't you think she would have label}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 ed herself in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I think she would have said that 'we're the shopkeepers' class', or the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , something like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you think she grew up thinking that, or did she have that view because of your father's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, you see, her father ... he had a shop. He had a hairdressing shop and it was carried on later, it was increased more into ... It was carried on by a granddaughter eventually, more into a toilet accessories, y
ou know. But he was really a wig-maker. I told you, didn't I? But of course, she knew that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 older}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 branches of his family, the old grandpa, were socially in a higher class. They'd no money, but socially, you know. That was the artist and the inventor, th
at part of the family. But she liked nice things and she liked nice people and I think she would consider she belonged to nice people. Oh, no, there wasn't anything of that. My father would despise anybody what would want to get to a position. So would Ba
rry, he's just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Do you remember anyone at that time being described as 'a real gentleman' or as 'a real lady'? Do you remember people using that expression at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If they had, what do you think it meant then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It would have meant someone who behaved like a lady. Not anybody of title or anything like that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 About behaviour and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember anybody moving from ... like you say your father wasn't striving for p
osition socially. Do you remember any people who did go up in the social scale, or down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I remember cousins who have married and improved their positions very much by marriage, but then of course they were about my age.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did they change their ways, at all? Did they change as people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They didn't change as people at all. I've just had a cousin ... the husband has died and she married ...}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 (tape cut)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, they were often ... yes, there were policeman around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In all your areas? I mean both in the cul-de-sac and in the ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, not many. Not many, but you know that you have to behave yourself if policeman were around, or the boys did (laughter) But we did
n't have any contact with them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did your mother or father ever say they'd call a policeman if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. That my father bad to do with policemen ... they used to get a lot of petty thefts from their shops, and especially fountain
 pens and playing cards. That's funny, they were things easier to take and easy to get rid of, you see. And he wasn't very severe about them but two young fellows, he did charge them because he thought, really, it was the best thing for their good that he
 
should do that. And they were sent to a school, you know; and they came back later to thank him. They did. For sending them, because ... when they were older, you know. So that was very ... He wouldn't like to do that, you know, be wouldn't like to punish
 unless he thought the punishment was really going to do good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How do you think the police treated the people round where you were, or were you not aware of the treatment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not, I was not aware of them. We very seldom saw one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you own your house in Beverley road, or was it rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The house, it would ... the shop. I wonder if he owned the shop? Yes, I think so. I think so, I don't think he was fond of paying rent.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't remember having a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't know anything about landlords, so we must have ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You weren't aware of a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was there ever a time - I mean in your younger days, for example - that you felt your parents were having a struggle to make ends meet?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 There was one time.
 I was 3 and my father had just opened another shop. It was a small ... sort of a bookstall and it was just by the Monument Bridge where the monument of this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Wilberforce}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  is and it was ... it turned out a very good investment, but then, of course, he hadn't
 any money and it was all he could do to get this shop. And the money had to be paid weekly, he had to pay for the papers each week ... it had to be sent, you know, or else they would have stopped his supplies. And one Saturday - or the day when he had to
 
take the money - he'd just got it all on the counter packed ready to take to the bank when a customer came in. I think two, perhaps. And then the money was gone and he didn't know what to do, and he came home and I can remember, dimly remember him lying o
n the couch. He was so upset, so shocked and it had upset him so much he was lying on the couch, and I had some ... knew it was that he hadn't got any money. I was only 3. Is your little girl 3?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, she will be in June.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, a little older than that. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 And}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8413823  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 I'd got my Saturday ha'penny it was, at 3 years old, and I went and put it in his hand and I said I don't want this you can have it'. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 (laughter) I don't think he ever forgot. And so, you see, I can remember what a tragedy that was. Well, eventu
ally he went around and borrowed - and I've never known him borrow anything ever, but he did. He borrowed from friends and just got over that difficulty. But that's the only time I ever heard of any ... because, you see, he was very wise and he wouldn't'v
e ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Speculated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Speculated, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And of course, having his own thing he was never out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no. Oh, no, no. Never out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And he didn't suffer from ill health or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He'd wonderful health. I've only known
 him ever have one illness and that was ... he had pneumonia when he was over 70, and my sister met the nurse that ... we had to get a nurse in to nurse him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How many schools did you go to altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I went to the infants' school that belonged 
to the church, at 3. Always went at 3, and I got a prize, a dolly, for good behaviour (laughter).
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What hours did you go when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We went at nine and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Come home for dinner, I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, we were close by. Oh usual times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And then you went back in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Usual times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long did you stay at that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At 7 you move up into the higher school, which was round the corner, into the bigger church school and I stayed there 'till I was 
... would it be 11? Yes, it would be 11 when I went to this high school, this Highgrave School. I was at those 3 schools, that's all, and I left terribly early and it was my own fault, you know. My mother was ill and I had to stay home to nurse her. I nur
s
ed her, and she was really very ill. It was the first time the 'flu came, really, to England, I think. And she didn't eat a thing for a fortnight, but she really didn't believe in eating in bed if you were ill. But anyhow, the doctor gave me instructions 
h
ow to cook one oyster for her, for her first meal. And just at that time we'd finished our term and the new term was starting and they'd gone up into what they called the science school when you started with new subjects, algebra ... what else was there? 
O
h, different subjects, you know, that we hadn't done before, and I'd missed a fortnight, I'd missed all the first lectures and I was so afraid of going back, you know. I knew I couldn't ... if you don't know the beginning of anything it's most difficult, 
i
sn't it? And so I talked round my parents. I was very naughty, I could get round them ... and talked round them to let me leave and go to classes for various things. And so the headmistress wrote and said such a pity for an intelligent girl to leave schoo
l
 ... You know, 13 was the leaving age; 14 you were staying a little extra. There was one girl staying 'till 16. She was the brains of the school. She was going to be a teacher. And so they did, and I left at 14 and went to painting classes which ... Just 
d
id the things I liked, you know. I went to painting classes and I did have a sampler sent up to South Kensington along with the students' work, flowers we did mostly. She was an A.R.A., the teacher who taught us. And then she gave up and, of course, I dro
p
ped it. I took up all sorts of things and then dropped it. And then I did art classes in the evenings, drawing classes; and then I did First Aid, and then Home Nursing. I had a medallion for that but I lost it, but everybody got one, it wasn't very hard, 
y
ou know. And I took bookkeeping classes and I never understood that double entry. I never understood why, and I dodged the exam. I didn't go. But later on when I was trying ... my husband was ... in the First World War he was exempt because of it being a 
o
ne-man business, but every ... now and again, every time we fought the Tribunal he was expecting he would be, and the last time he had to appear before the Tribunal he really thought that they would take him because they were getting so tight for new men,
 
and the Armistice was called just in time, so he didn't have to go. But he was volunteering. He volunteered and was doing night work driving troops through London, you know from various railway stations and in the meantime I was helping him ... I'd got th
e
 children in the country and I came up when he was on those duties and I was opening his office in the mornings, and trying to go on with my bookkeeping because I should have had it to do if he'd gone. And he couldn't explain to me why all these things sh
o
uld go ... and I didn't do anything, I left it. He managed his bookkeeping perfectly, without understanding, I think (laughter). What else did I ...? Oh, I had a violin and I went to violin classes, and my brothers declared that whilst I was practicing th
e
 cat went out of the room and was sick (laughter). But what really did happen: a plumber came to put on a tap and he did put it on all askew! (laughter) So you can tell what my violin-playing was like, can't you. I did manage to play in the orchestra of t
he Sunday meeting they had for men at P.S.A. I don't know whether you've heard of them, they were very popular, the P.S.A for men. But that ... mine was hidden with the sound of the others.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you have any regrets about your education, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 W
ell, I think I should have had a more orderly brain and been more orderly if I'd stayed longer. But as for other things, I'd said once I haven't got much education but I've got by. I've never really missed it very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you think you benefited from attending school, though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, of course! You learnt, of course, writing and reading particularly and all those kind of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Which of the schools do you remember the most clearly? Or do you remember them equally well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, equally well. I liked school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, taking that first school, then, it was a Church of England School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was it mixed boys and girls in the infants'?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I expect so, I didn't ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about in the junior, the higher stages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 After that, there were no mixing. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That school, was it quite near your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did you think about that school? You say you liked school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't remember being unhappy at school for any period of time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. We had nice teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At both schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Do you remember what the teachers stressed as important? Not counting school work now, but things like how you behaved, manners, punctuality, ways of speaking. Do you remember anything particular that they stressed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't. I don't remember. Perhaps they weren't very ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Perhaps you didn't do anything very naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, no, I wasn't inclined to be ... I mean, they didn't insist on very much, but the behaviour was good, generally,
 in the school. It really was. It's altered very much from what I hear, of the children being rude to their teachers and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't remember that from your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no. No, there was nobody cheeky to the teachers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You would be caned.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At both schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I did have the cane once. Yes. The teacher went out of the room leaving a class of girls ... leaving ... not to talk and she sat one girl in the front
 saying - I forget which school it was - she left one girl in the front to tell who had spoken, and we all did. There was a whole chatter going on round the school 'till someone saw the teacher coming back. And then she asked this girl who had spoken and 
I was nearest to her, so she just said me. 'Twasn't fair, of course, but of course you couldn't get out of it. Oh, it wasn't much, it was very slight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were you ever caned at any other time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were there any other punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. The
re were sort of rewards. But when I went to this Highgrave School there was a board, a notice board up and the girl who had done the best work during the week had her name up, and my name was going up for one week and I went home and told my mother. I was
 
delighted. And when I got back on the Monday morning it wasn't there, and it was the name of the girl who was the niece of the art master, and I think our headmistress was a little bit sweet on the art master. She put her name on the board, and so my fath
e
r went down to see about it 'cos I'd told him, you see, that my name was to go on the board. And she said that she thought that Bella had been such a nice lady-like sort of girl it would be a good example for the others to have her name ... Well! What do 
you think of that! She was horrid. She really was horrid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The girl, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, the headmistress, was horrid. And she offered to change it. My father said no, he wouldn't have it changed. I don't know what he said to her but I know that he woul
d quietly put her in her place. She didn't marry the art master but she married the chemistry master. He had 2 children, he was a widower, so I felt sorry for those 2 children. I can remember her now. She was a little dark person with a mean little face, 
rather, and not anybody that you'd have any affection for, want to give her a present or anything like that. But still, we were all treated quite all right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your mother ever go up to the school for anything, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. she would have done, I think, if she'd had to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At either school were there any parent's evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They weren't invited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, there wasn't anything like that, no. She sometimes came up to meet me if she was going to take me, on rare occasion
s, to buy material to make me a dress or something. And do you know, I knew what I wanted and I wouldn't have anything else, and I remember her coming out and saying 'well, really! If you give people such trouble I shan't bring you out any more to choose 
your clothes'. That was only a threat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember if they took an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes. Well, I don't know about the exact work ... Yes, they did. Of course, they took an interest in anything that we did, but I don't think t
hey knew how much the schools were supposed to teach us then, or what they were really teaching us. You see, we only had reading, writing and arithmetic and a little grammar, very little. And then when I got to the second school those subjects weren't str
essed at all, so I never had much English grammar teaching.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What subjects were stressed at the second school? At Highgrave School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, they did history, you see, and more grammar, and art. I could get good high marks for drawing. I liked that. 
And composition; I liked that, too. And I don't think I was very honest in my composition because once I got a little bit of a rhyme about Florence Nightingale and the question was 'what would you like to be'. Well, I thought I could work that in, I said 
I
 would like to be a lady doctor, and I got good marks for the ... and I finished up with this rhyme about Florence Nightingale, The Lady With The Lamp. And she thought I really meant to be a lady doctor and she came to me later on and she said 'you know, 
I
 think you would really be a very good subject. I'll enquire for you about the various training schemes'. I wouldn't have dared ... I hadn't the confidence in myself to do that and, of course, I hadn't the brain, either, I think. But I said to one young f
riend of mine who's a medical student, 'I should never have had the confidence, it's such a responsibility. How do you feel about accepting that?' She said 'that comes'. She said, 'during your studies you get that'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I just wondered whether there were a
ny gangs in the school, or groups? I don't mean gangs going around with knives, or anything, I mean little cliques of girls that kept themselves separate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't think so. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 
It was more the friends you came and went to school with, you see. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Friends yo
u made. I had several ... quite a list of acquaintances that we walked up and down, home and back with, you know, but I didn't make particular friends there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did anybody of your family go with you to school? Or did you go on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I went on my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about when you were 3, when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, I expect my mother took me, but I don't remember. But it was only across the road so somebody would take me. It wasn't far away.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes. I 
had a bicycle at 15 and not many girls were riding bicycles at that time. It was just at the time when Mrs. Bloomer came out with her cycling bloomers. But we had dresses to your ankle with an elastic strap going the ankle that you had to slip your feet i
n to keep your dress right round to the ankle. And you had a guard on the side, you know, to keep these voluminous dresses out of the wheel spokes. But oh, yes, I had a bicycle. We used to do quite a bit of cycling. That was one of the pleasures.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever go for walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, we used to walk. Just with your girlfriends, you know. We used to walk quite a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you do that before you left school, too, the walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever go fishing, or was that just for boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. None of us would go fishing. They didn't fish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your father go fishing at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, he had no time for any ... really ....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 For that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At all of your schools, do you remember any children who were l
eft out of things, who were lonely and shunned by the other children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't. Well, there was one poor girl ... Is your mike on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Do you want me to switch it off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 ... Too much to rebuild it, and so they've had to take it do
wn and they're selling that piece of land and they're enlarging a good church hall that they had on the other side, and they're enlarging that and making that into a small church because the church now is a big church that holds 800 people, and it was ful
l
 for my wedding. An uncle of mine who came late had to stand. But they weren't using the little gallery upstairs, but the downstairs was really ... It seems such a pity because it's still ... My father came up with a committee to inspect a church at Ilfor
d that had just been built and it was built on this same plan, it's sort of hexagonal inside and oh, it's so plain. And then it has a little ... oh, dear, word's gone, but you know, that you go back in the church where the Altar is, that's the ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The Chancel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The Chancel? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Yes, where the choir sits and the ... yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That is built like that and it's exceedingly nice. But still ... there, it's gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were engaged for those 2 years did you still only see each other just occasionally like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That's all. Just occasionally. We wrote letters ... corresponded
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But I wasn't quite clear. You were saying the time you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 were on}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  the donkey and he took the photograph, you were 18 I think you said?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, I should be 18 then, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And then you said that you were engaged for 2 years, but you'd known him for 6 years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
It would be 6 years. You see, we were engaged for 2 years and when we were married I was 28 and he was 27. Well, really, he was 26 because there was a year and 3 m
onths between us. We were married in June and by August, he was 26, you see. So let me see, what does that make it? No, I was 19, I must have been, then, and he was 18 and 6 years would bring that ... No, I must have been only 17. No, he ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He was 17, do you think? You think that you knew him for about 10 years before you actually got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I only knew him for ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 About 8 years, would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Wait a minute ... Yes, it would be 10 years before we got married. I must have known hi
m 5 years before we were engaged, and it would be 7 years altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And when you said you wanted the long engagement he didn't mind that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, he would rather not have waited, but he didn't care.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did his sister have a very big wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, big for them, you know. They had a marquee put over the small garden and lots of friends. Not a fashionable wedding, you know, we would say, but a nice wedding and a nice wedding dress and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was it quite a long time after he got your letter saying you wanted to break it off that they had the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, it wasn't so very long afterwards, but she wrote me a nice letter saying she was very sorry at what she'd heard, but would I still be her bridesmaid, you see. And so, of cour
se, I came up, and whether he'd persuaded his sister to write and say would I still be ... I don't think so because it was all arranged, and her sister-in-law was a friend of mine and we ... you know, we should have done things together. I got to know her
 up in London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And your very original first meeting with him, was that at the church, when you were staying in London?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. The very first meeting was ... it was just before. It would be when I went to my cousin's wedding, you see, and they hadn'
t got anybody to take photographs and he was doing quite a bit of photography then, and amateur photographer, and someone said 'go and ask Arthur Bucknell, he would come and take some photographs'. And he did. Well, that was just at the time, you remember
 King ... was it Edward who got ... he was just going to be crowned and he got appendicitis? Yes, well, it was just at that time. Well, the decorations were all up for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 Coronation}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  that didn't take place just then, and so another cousin of mine said, 'com
e on, let's all go round on a bus and see these decorations at night', and they got him to go - I supposed they arranged it when he came over to take the photographs - and she had left her brother-in-law to look after me, my cousin, her new brother-in-law
 
... an old friend, I'd known him. And he went with us and he sat with my older cousin, and my husband ... No. She took the ... she was lively and she took Arthur on her seat with him and gave me the prim old brother-in-law to be my companion. He was very 
g
ood, he did take care of me. He took me cycling over Hampstead Heath with a friend of his who was lately a solicitor. And these two young fellows, we got in an awful thunderstorm, and we rushed in ... they had to take shelter. They rushed into the ... wha
t do you call it at the top of the ...? Jack Straw's Castle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Me, in a public house! I'd never been in a public house in my life! Well, no women over went in except these drunken or gin-drinking old women. No decent women ever went into a pub
lic house. Never!! I did feel uncomfortable. I was glad when the rain stopped and we could get out and go home. And to later in the ... this was between that and the outing, I passed him in the street, he didn't recognise me. I didn't feel very compliment
ed. But that was before the outing, the Sunday School outing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you fell off the donkey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes. No, it was a pony. Yes, it was a pony, and my word, did it gallop. I didn't mind because I could hold on, but when the photograph was taken of me - I've lost it, I don't know where it went - clinging round it's neck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have a honeymoon when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We went to Switzerland. Not many young people went abroad in those days. We thought we were very adventurous. Oh, it was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 A fortnight. We went to Lucerne.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Had you been abroad before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So I expect you were very excited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, very. And I haven't been since, except that the family, for our Si
lver Wedding, instead of giving a silver present bought us a ticket to go back because my husband had said always, 'we must go again some day', you know, but always too busy to leave his business, but of course, they took the tickets and we had to go. Als
o, they gave a big illustrated greeting, you know, Swiss pictures on it, and everything, to us, and we enjoyed it just as much the second time as the first.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you get many wedding presents? I remember you said that somebody gave you a nice brooch, who'd worked for your father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, 150, small and large, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Was it the custom for, say, certain members of the family to give certain things? Like in some families the bride's mother always gives the linen. Did you have any customs like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, but our old grandma, she was very fond of copper and she gave her grandchildren copper kettles. My daughter, now that's in the country, I passed it on to her, and they've got a very large room with a long stone fireplace and big log fires whe
re this copper kettle stands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 After your honeymoon you came to London, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Where did you live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We lived in Hampstead, in King Henry's Road, not far from here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And you lived there until you were bombed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. We had a maisonette, the two lower floors, and we let the ... my husband let the top floor flat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did he own the house himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And you lived there until, what? About 1941 or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When we were bombed, it was '44.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What was your husband's job when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, he was a builder and decorator, and later on they made their premises, stables that they had at the back of the ... They had a house, they got a house in that road where their business is ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was it a family business, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, his father and him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was his father the first one to start it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, the father was a country boy whose father gave him a solid gold sovereign to come up to make his fortune in London. And he marri
ed Grandma, and that helped ... very young, you know ... and yes, he built it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Had your husband ever worked in any other concern or done any other job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, he added a bit of estate agency to his building. He really ... as a boy he was in an architect's office for a little while.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that with a view to becoming a fully qualified architect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I don't know why he didn't continue with that, I never asked him, but whether his parents couldn't afford to give him a fully ...
 full training. I should think that was it because he liked it and ... would have done ... And then at 19 he opened an office, took over a shop that was opposite there, their stable, which is now a garage ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In King Henry's Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, in Regent'
s Park Road quite near. It's nearer to Primrose Hill, close to Primrose Hill. And he added this estate agency, but the building was primarily the ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The building work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He carried on in that business all his working life, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes. But of course, in the War - he was 60, then, when we were bombed he was 60, and he died of hardening of the arteries and gradually ... that must have been coming on for quite a time. It may have been ... I asked the doctor once if postponed shock mig
ht have been any cause. He said 'might have been, there's no knowing'. And so, of course, he was getting less able to carry on from that time on. And so we had various managers but they couldn't make a success. The managers. Some of them were quite good m
en, but financially ... I think things were very difficulty just after the war. They couldn't make a success.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 There was so little building going on, wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. And so then my son, Barry, he was trained as a mechanical engineer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At Daimler's, was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, he did an apprenticeship with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Daimler\rquote s,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  but he got his qualifications for the Mechanical Engineers' Society, you know. And then he came in and carried on as a garage. That was principally, and gradually they've let the build
ing drop. But they have an electrical branch of the building, and that carried on, and that's still carrying on from the same offices as the garage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So he came in and ran the garage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were first married do you think your husband liked his work, or did he dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, he loved it. Yes, he loved it, and he was very good, but he wasn't so keen on the financial side. He did his own bookkeeping, he always had a typist and at one time a very efficient bookkeeper, but he wasn'
t so keen on the money. He would let customers go on that he wasn't quite sure about, you know, and was not really keen enough. Of course, that's what I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How did you manage about budgeting? Did you know what he earned when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, because ... Oh, yes, he took out of the business }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13117750 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 3 a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How much of that was his and how much was yours?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, he paid all the bills of the gas and electricity and everything like that, you know. I never paid any of those bills 
'till after he died. And he bought my clothes as well. But just merely for food ... and also we had a customer, a butcher there, and they would exchange bills, you see. I mean, he would supply us with meat, as much as we wanted all the time and then when 
he'd had work done Arthur sent him the bill, they balanced up. So I didn't have to trouble about that, paying bills. And I had 25 shillings a week for housekeeping, and I had money over and we had lots of visitors. And we had a very young }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 bachelor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  parson at
 that time who lived quite close and he came in to supper every Sunday evening - meat supper, you know, and all that kind of thing, and still have plenty of money. I don't remember, but I got all the clothes I wanted, all paid for that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You paid for your clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He paid for the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He paid for the clothes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about things like ... if you wanted to buy a present for somebody, those little extra things, did that some out of the 25 shillings?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, we used to do that between us, I think. I can't quite remember. But I never had to save or scrape, not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I was just wondering whether you had a little money just to spend on yourself, or little things you wanted for yourself. Not clothing, bu
t just those little extra toilet things, how did you manage for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It seemed I had plenty for those little oddments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Out of the 25 shillings, you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, I had because I was so proud because I occasionally bought myself a blouse, but 
a blouse wouldn't cost much in those days. You know, that 25 shillings for we two was sufficient. I had a cousin living near and her husband was ... he was assistant something in the Guardians, Assistant Registrar. She had 18 shillings for her housekeepin
g and when I stayed there I was amply fed. Doesn't it seem ridiculous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, amazing. Did you and your husband discuss money, how the money should be spent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You didn't have discussions about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, no, he wouldn't bother about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Now in that house you said you let off the top floor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 There were 2 flats upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were they self-contained? Did they have their own kitchen ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, self-contained ... they didn't have their ... Yes, they had their own kitchen an
d everything, but not their own front door. The general front door there was.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But otherwise they didn't share any facilities with you, except that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, not at all. There were 2 that were with us all the time we were there 'till the last War
, one elderly lady and her younger friend were on the first floor above.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They were quite separate from you? They didn't have any meals with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How many rooms were there in your part of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, my husband kept splitting them up and altering them as the need grew (laughter), you see. He was very good at that kind of thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What was there at first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At first we had 2 bedrooms. We had 3 rooms upstairs. Wait a minute, did we split that one? No, that was lat
er. We had the large room which we made a drawing room; this was on the top floor. And our bedroom, yes, and then a smaller one. Yes, that was on that floor: three. And then later, of course, as I say, our large bedroom we split up for two small ones for 
a living-in girl, you know, and one of the children. And downstairs we had a big awfully ugly old kitchen with a great big double stove side ovens. Burnt tons of coal and didn't keep anything warm. We changed that afterwards; and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  with French win
dows opening onto the garden, which was very nice. The kitchen at the front, yes, and then beside the bathroom and lavatory.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was there a basement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 This was the ... well, it was a semi-basement. Yes, it was level at the back, you know, with the g
arden, but just a little ... like most of the houses round here. Of course, later on that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 in ... you wouldn't want how they altered it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You told me that you got a girl to live in after you'd had the twins, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have anybody living in before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, after I had Barry, he was the first - the twins were born a year and 8 months later - I tried little girls, tiny young girls coming daily and they weren't ... oh, they were just a nuisance, most of them, and so
 I had to have somebody permanently after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you remember the first one you had, for example, that lived in permanently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, the first one was really a relative of friends of mine, and their parents died and they were giving up their hom
e. She had brothers and they wanted something for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 Louey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 to do. - she was a very capable girl - where she could live. You see, there was nothing but domestic work and so they wrote to me and said could she come as a mother's help, which she did, and she was
 very efficient. That was very nice. I was able to give my time to these premature babies, you see, I gave my whole time to them, keeping them alive, and so I was able.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she come to you before they were born, or afterwards?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Afterwards, yes, 
because when they were born I had a little nurse. Just by luck we got this person who lived near. Our own nurse we'd engaged was far away and this little ... she'd never had a normal baby for 12 months. She'd kept them alive in all kinds of ways, and she 
kept ours alive. And I had this little }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 Louey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
. The mother came and persuaded me to give her a chance, she was a little slow in the brain. And I had this }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 Louey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 and oh, dear, it was a nuisance, this nurse wouldn't have her in the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She wouldn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No. Not with the babies. Well, she wouldn't have any noise where those babies were. But Louey told somebody ... they were asking her about these babies ... she was there at the time, you know and she said ... It had just come in at that time that the mate
rnity allowance was 30 shillings and she'd heard about this, and she said to these people, telling them they were little babies, she said, 'you see, Mrs. Bucknell got the 30 shillings for them because they were two little'uns'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How early were they, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
They were 8 months. Only 8 months. But they were very small: 3 lbs. 6, and 3 lbs. 10 ozs. They said I'd neglected myself, not looked after them. Well, I said to the doctor before they were born - you didn't have any pre-natal examination, you kno
w. He didn't give you any, and no clinics, you know, or that kind of thing. And I said to him 'Doctor, I think there's more than one baby here', I said 'I'm sure I feel more limbs'. 'No, I think not', he said, and then of course, when they arrived there w
e
re two. Then, when I had the third baby he said, I'm afraid it's twins again, but very small', and I said - he was a long time being born - and I said 'I don't think so, Doctor, I think it's one boy', because we in my family we go alternately, a boy and a
 
girl, a boy and a girl, and I seemed at accept that we should do the same, you see. We had one boy and 2 girls. And it was one boy, you see. But he didn't know that, the doctor didn't know. They didn't test their hearts, they hadn't got any appliances or 
methods of testing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you go regularly every month to see the doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not like people do now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You just went to him to tell him that your periods had stopped and were you pregnant, and of course he said, 'yes', but they didn't mak
e any particular examination.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They didn't weigh you regularly, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, no. No pre-natal care. Perhaps he was a little old-fashioned, he was a dear old thing and quite good to us in most ways, but he didn't ... there wasn't ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And you had the same doctor for when you had Barry, too, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He had died ... wait a minute. Oh, yes, I had him for Barry. I was talking about the later one, David. Yes, we had the same one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And so you had this nurse. She was a private nurse, I suppose? When you had the twins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When I had Barry I had, oh, a real old-fashioned maternity nurse, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you get her from a hospital?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. Oh, no, nothing to do with hospitals in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She was a private nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, she was a private midwife. And then last time ... of course, the twins came premature and, of course, no preparation made for them, and we happened to get this nurse who was so clever with them. My sister-in-law, my husband's sister, she said ..
. she'd been talking to this nurse, she'd met her, and she said 'if ever I have another baby I shall get that Nurse So-and-so who lives just round the corner'. And so I thought of her first and we sent for her, and she was on holiday but she was in Kilbur
n
 and so we said 'well, we must get her from Kilburn'. Well, at that time no buses of tramcars or anything ran on Sunday morning, not 'till midday. My husband couldn't get there, so he got out his bicycle, he said he'd go on his bicycle to try and get her 
-
 found he'd got a puncture. So he stays off mending this puncture and the doctor said 'why doesn't Bucknell get off?' And I said, 'look he's got a puncture, he can't go, but he'll go quickly'. When he got there she was in church. He got to the church and 
got her out and she came, and put his bicycle on top of a cab, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2913224\charrsid8413823 old-fashioned}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 four-wheelers, you know, and got there half an hour before they were born. That old doctor, really! He was terrible, he never explained the case to her, nor anything, and he went o
n reading his newspaper, just flung her a word or so, and she carried on. She kept her bonnet on because they were supposed to wear a cap, or something, whilst they were there. And so she delivered the babies. But of course, they were no trouble. Oh, no t
rouble at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Being so small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, they were so small. Half an hour between them. That's all, but they looked just like a couple of skinned rabbits, that bluey colour and oh, they were ugly, poor little things! I said to this nurse once - she wa
s rather dignified and she was very keen on her work. She had been an orphan and she'd been a children's nurse and she'd wanted to do maternity work, so she'd saved up until she could get the proper training and she was very, very good. Well, afterwards s
he took over a cr\'e8
che in a very high church association. She was the matron there. But I said to her - we were talking about them, and I said, 'Nurse, if you put a little pipe in their mouth they'd look like two wrinkled old Irish women'. 'Oh, Mrs. Bucknell
!', she said. And when they cried, you know, they went 'eee, eee, eee'. And I said 'aren't they just like two little kittens, the noise they make?' Oh, she wouldn't admit that, no, they were too precious to make fun of them like that. But a cousin came an
d
 I said - we had them in one cradle with a hot water bottle between them, in one normal ... for one baby, you know, and they'd plenty of room - and this cousin came to look at them and I said 'did you think they would be so funny, Gladys', and she says, '
no, I didn't!'. (laughter) So you can tell what they were like. But they grew out of that, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long did she stay with you, that nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She could only stay a fortnight, and this other one wasn't due for another 6 weeks, I think, and we 
had to have her, we'd engaged her, you see. She wouldn't have been any use to keep those babies alive. She was nice and a good nurse, but her one thought was keeping the room spotless, and everything for the doctor. Well, our doctor didn't care so much ab
out that, it was the patient he thought about. But then came another one and she was a fat, jolly person, but very slap-dash. She couldn't have done it. Weren't we fortunate?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, you were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Very fortunate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Because it was that nurse, I think you told me, that went out and got a special teat, didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, that was the clever one, yes. Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What was it that she got?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They called them Sockslip bottles. They were teeny little ordinary bottle shape, but they'd got t
he top fitted with this teeny, teeny little teat and she managed to get them to take that, until they could take the proper nipple, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But she gave them your own milk from this bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, she ... we got a pump and it took half an hour to pump it and an hour to give them it every two hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she keep on through the night, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
For the first 2 nights she kept ... yes, on all the night. And she had a little bed put by at the end of my bed, and had a nap during the day, slept d
uring the day a little. She was very strict. Of course, I wasn't ill, you know, and I was kept in bed for ... what? a fortnight, I think, but you were ... as a rule, you know, before then you were ... not go out for a month, you were an invalid for a mont
h
 in the days before that, supposed to be. And she made me lie down and sleep in the afternoon, and I was bored, I didn't want to go to sleep, and so I had a writing pad under my pillow and I'd snuggle this out while she was asleep. She heard the page as i
t came up and took it away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 After 2 weeks you were allowed to get up, were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I went out at the end of 2 weeks, a little walk up Primrose Hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You didn't actually have to stay in bed all the time for 2 weeks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long did you have to stay in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I don't remember, but I should think it would be a week. I'm not sure, but of course, with Barry, the first one, he was ... well, rather difficult. I was 36 hours in labour with him. Mary, one of my daughters who's a nurse, sh
e said that would never have been allowed. Do you know, during the last hour he came in ... Labour began at 7 in the morning and at 10 that night he came and said it wouldn't be long, and he wasn't born 'till 10 the next night. And when he came in the las
t
 time before then I said 'Oh, Doctor, haven't you got something, but he said 'well, I have, but I don't think you're quite at the end yet and, 'he said', I do believe that a normal birth is best'. So we went on. But do you know, I've never ... well, I've 
not had much pai}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12812202\charrsid8413823 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  in my life, but that was severe. And the last hour I couldn't see ... I could only see black.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You must have been exhausted, too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, it was, you know. It took you a long time to recover. Had stitches, of course.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But it was a normal delivery in the end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, it was a normal delivery, but he had quite a long ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He didn't give you any chloroform, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In those days people were kept more in ignorance, weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you know what to expect in childbirth, as women do today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, no, I didn't know ... I knew a bit. I'd got to know as much as I could, you know, but it wasn't a terrible lot. But you didn't know that things could be made easier by anything. You knew it woul
d be painful in any case, and yet it isn't with everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I had exercises and preparation which helped me a great deal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, if you've no special difficulty that does help, and there was no special difficulty with me. But of course, I was old. 
I was 29 when Barry was born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That can make it a bit more difficult.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
The doctor said, 'if Mrs. Bucknell were 19 ...'But still, people over 30 and even 40 get over it, don't they? Have their babies now quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did he weigh when he was born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Six and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you feed him yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, yes. Yes, he was quite a healthy baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In those days, thinking about Barry, how long did you go on giving them just your own milk? Until you started giving them something else?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, you were supposed to go on giving your own milk 'till 9 months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you do that with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I think I did. You'd give them, perhaps, a little something else, you know. But do you know, at that time they said don't give children ordinary greens, green vegetables, 'till they're 18 months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So he didn't have any 'till he was 18 months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, I don't suppose so. No, he didn't, not 'till he was 18 months. I went by the present-day advice, you know, as to what to give children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you remember when he first had any solid food at all? You know, like ... what did he have first for solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I should think it would be mince ... a little meat for them. Of course, they had a little bread, or bread and butter, a little.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And porridge, or cereal, did they have anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, we gave them ... Yes, porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When did you start him on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I think I started a little before he was weaned. I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You mean a little before 9 months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, but not so early as they do now. You'd never have dreamt of giving a child anything like that ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you started to wean him was it gradually? How did you wean him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't quite remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was it gradually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, gradually. An
d not for ... I don't think it took very long because he ... I didn't give him a bottle. No, he never had a bottle at all, but he could drink, you see, by that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You mean you weaned him by giving him something from a cup?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, yes, and then 
they had ... they always had a lot of milk to drink. In fact when we were young, in my young days, that was our permanent drink. We had milk with boiling water poured in to warm it sufficient to drink, and drank heaps of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you did wean him did he seem to mind, was it a struggle or did it come easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't think so. He never bothered a great deal about his food, Barry. He took what you gave him and it didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have any difficulties at all in feeding him yourself or did it come quite easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, it came. It came easily.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Who gave you advice if you needed advise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, if there was anything really troublesome you'd go to your doctor. That was the only thing you could do, there was no ... there weren't the clinics in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So advice like when to start weaning him, that kind of thing ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, you would use your own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 judgment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , I think, about that, or if they seemed quite well ... With my last baby, David, I fed him for ... what was it? 
... five months or more and I wondered if he was ... if I ought to go on longer so I asked the doctor. The doctor said, 'well, no, you must stop. You must wean him now'. He said, 'He's all right, but it's wearing you. It's too much for you, you mustn't do
 it'. Perhaps I was feeling he wasn't satisfied, or something, but he said stop it, so I had to put him on to foods at 5 months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you had Barry, for example, did you feed him at certain fixed times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were they sort of a certain number of hours apart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, four hours when they grew older. Well, I think we started at 3 and then went on to 4 hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Who told you about starting them at 3, who gave you that advice, would that be the nurse you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, because the 
nurse I had for Barry was just an old-fashioned old nurse who ... well, she would give you the old ... you know, the old-fashioned ideas. You hear it from different people, I think, different people who have babies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was your mother with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, my mother wasn't near, she was away in Yorkshire, you know, and I dare say she would if I'd asked, but ... I can't think. I think in a way you used your own common sense, as much as anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I wondered if in those days you would have heard ... would it have been from your friends, do you think, or books, or the nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, it would be the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The doctor would have told you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. I might have read some books, but I don't think so, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you stick quite exactly to certain hours or were you flexible about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I've never been so very strict about things, if I thought it would ease the situation to give them a little at some time I suppose I would do it, but I kept it exactly as far as I could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was your aim?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
They had a six o'clock feed, always, before going to bed, you know. But Barry didn't sleep. I think he might have been fed again. When he began teething, both he and the younger boy David, they woke up ... he woke up and he 
was a terror to get to sleep again, soon after he got to bed he woke up. Oh, yes, he was a terror.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So what did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I wouldn't bring him downstairs, I went up. I remember one night I was busy, I think I hadn't a help at that time, 
and I went up 10 times during the evening to try and get him to sleep. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 
And he would say, if I was there, 'Daddy, come a 'Barry, Daddy come a 'Barry', and if his father was there he'd say, 'Mummy come a 'Barry, Mummy come a 'Barry'. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 My sister took him home 
when the twins were born - at least, Mother took him - and my sister who was newly married, she took him over from Mother. And she said 'that poor little chap', she said, 'when he went to sleep and he cried for his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 mummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  or his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 daddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 she felt so terrible, but she said one night she'd taken him to meet the Chapel people leaving ... her friends, you know, were leaving and she took him to meet them, and that night he said, '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Daddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  come Barry, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Mummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 come Barry, all the Chapel people come Barry'. So she said she didn't worry after that, it was just he didn't want to be alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If he was fast asleep at a feeding time would you wake him for the feed or would you wait until ...?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I should think you would wake, probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You would wake him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I should think ... Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And if he cried before the normal time you would sometimes feed him, would you, as you said to ease the situation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, if I thought he was hungry, you see. But that didn't happen often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He stuck to the time schedule, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, yes. He was pretty good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did you do if he didn't seem to be hungry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't remember him ever not seeming hungry. And the twins were always ready for their food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And when you did feed him did you let him go on feeding as
 long as he liked at the breast or did you take him off after a certain number of minutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't remember, but I gave him both sides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I wondered if you let him go on 'till he seemed satisfied or if at that time you were told to stop after a certain length of time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I wasn't told anything about that. As I say, you had to use your own }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 
judgment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Just 'till they were satisfied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Of course, if a baby's an easy feeder you don't remember things so much as if you have a terrible struggle with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. ... Terrible struggle with them, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you think when Barry was a baby that it did any harm to a baby to be left to cry, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I didn't like to leave them to cry. I don't think he ever did cry withou
t some reason that I couldn't settle. I knew why he was crying, as a rule. I mean I've never had babies crying and you didn't know why, you couldn't find the cause. No, I'd never had any need to leave them, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you punish him when he was naugh
ty? At what sort of age did you think a child needed correction? I don't mean necessarily hitting him, but correcting him, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't remember. You would correct him in some way, but I can't remember quite how. It wasn't much. They really didn
't need it. They weren't really terribly naughty. He did things that ... they weren't really naughty it was more ... 'cos he was very inventive and it was the trouble that caused that gave me trouble. No, he wasn't very naughty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What sort of things?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, when they were quite little, one day when I had this help she got sciatica and she was very ill and I had the doctor to her. And so that morning I fed Barry and the twins, but I hadn't bathed them - they were about 2, and he would be 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8413823  1/2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , I s
hould think. And I thought I would go and give Louey her breakfast and then come down and dress them. And they were playing in the kitchen, the old big kitchen we had then, and they'd got a wooden horse. And before I went upstairs ... there was a big kitc
h
en cupboard there and I kept my stores in there, china as well, but on the upper shelves I kept my stores and any household things, and I remembered about the catch being broken on there, so I jammed it with cardboard so that Barry couldn't get that open 
t
o look for anything. And I heard them tapping this horse with something and I thought they were playing with the horse, that's quite all right. They sounded so happy, I didn't open the door. I thought, I'll go and get Louey ready for the doctor before I c
o
me and bath them'. And when I came down and opened the door, well, he'd got to this cupboard and managed to get the door open and found a pot of ... We had ... My husband in connection with his building we had to send to some general stores for something 
t
hey needed and he said 'look at this catalogue, there might be something in this that you could use', and I looked through and I saw that they had black shoe polish, Cherry Blossom'. And they were all wearing little black leather shoes and we were using a
 
lot and I said, 'oh, yes, get them to send me a dozen of these Cherry Blossoms'. And they were in this cupboard, and he'd opened 10 to paint the horse, the twins helping him. You can imagine!! It was all over this kitchen dresser. Well, the paint came off
 
before the blacking came off. It was all over themselves, and the girls had cream dressing gowns on. And one had a thick moustache of this black paint. I picked her up and ran upstairs to Louey to show her to try and make her smile because the girl was so
 
miserable, so sorry for herself. And this was Easter Monday and I thought when I saw them 'well, this is my Easter Day'. And that was the first time my husband's lunch wasn't ready for him when he came in, but it wasn't ... He wanted to go back to the off
i
ce, he had some work to do, and so he didn't know about all this 'till he got in for his lunch. Oh, it was all right. It was nothing serious, you know, bowls and bowls and bowls of soda water and all that kind of thing. But, I mean, you wouldn't punish a 
boy for a thing like that when he was amusing his little sisters, would you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, and how were they to know it wasn't all right, at that age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, and I hadn't even said, 'don't try to get this cupboard open' or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When the babies were little, Barry and then the twins, did you husband do anything to help with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, he was very good. You see, my mother took ... He didn't as a rule, but my mother took Barry. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 She'd come up to take him well before this next baby was due, to take him to Yorkshire and she was landed there because the next ... you know, came immediately. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And she took Barry back, she stayed a week or more and poor Mother, she hadn't been used to doing any cooking or anything for some time, and this aw
ful old kitchen at that time, with the terrible cooking and the nurse we had at the time would say, 'Mrs. I'd like Mrs. Bucknell to have so-and-so' and poor Mother had to go in and cook it for her. I think now how marvelous it was. Anyhow, she took Barry 
b
ack and he came back with the whooping cough. And I said to the doctor he'd been with the twins some time before I found out it was whooping cough, and I said to the doctor and I'm afraid they've got it, Doctor, because one of them was coughing. He said, 
'
oh, dear, oh, dear', as much as to say you can't hope now to keep them, you know. But do you know, I really think it helped them to get on because they coughed, and although they don't whoop at that tiny age, it expanded their lungs. You see, they were bo
rn with pigeon breasts, like this, and this coughing ... But one day one of them was turning blue. I turned her upside down and smacked her back and managed to get it free, but they got over that quite all right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Amazing, isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 At what age were they ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
So at that time, you see, my husband and I had to ... during the night we had to ... Well, the twins ... Barry came back after 2 months and they were born just before he went, they would be two months old, 2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8413823 
 1/2}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  months
 old and we had to ... he got up ... we had to get up to one or the other of them about every hour, you see, and he would get up alternately with me. And I said to him once, one night 'wouldn't it be lovely if we could get 2 hours' consecutive sleep'.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 This was with their coughing, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, with their coughing, yes. And he was very good, then. Oh, he would be in any emergency he was at once ready, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 To help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You fed them yourself, didn't you? Breast fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, I fed them to 5 months, and then it wasn't sufficient, they had to have ... But we just went on to milk and ... what did I have? I had a certain amount of ... Some special kind of milk, I think and a certain amount of cream, a spoonful 
of cream in the milk each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And so you weaned them on to a bottle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I was very lucky. My husband had a customer near, a young doctor, and he died and my husband had to ... I think it was clear out a lot of things there and he came across a little 
book, a doctor's book about the feeding of babies, the treatment of these special babies, you know. And I had that little book and I learnt a lot from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How interesting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Wasn't it? And that was fortunate, wasn't it? And that was how I got this idea of the cream.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So then you weaned them on to bottles at 5 months, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, for a time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long did they stay on bottles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I think we gradually gave them a little food, I should think, from about 6 months, we should give them a little something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And when did they stop having bottles, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We shouldn't keep on after 9 months?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not even with the twins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't think so. They got on to food, quite small amounts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But didn't they have any milk from a bottle after 9 months? Even though they had been so tiny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They'd have it all from a cup would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 After 9 months ... Maybe we might have kept on a little with them with the bottle, but I don't r
emember them having a bottle very long. Yes, they could take it from a cup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were they difficult to wean onto a bottle or didn't they seem to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4469069\charrsid8413823 mind?}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  Do you remember any difficulty over that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They didn't refuse the bottle? 'Cos they'd had a bit from a bottle ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
They had the bottle first, you see, they had those tiny little bottles. No, they didn't refuse a bottle at all. I've never had any difficulty with my children with feeding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Lucky, really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, very lucky, because some do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
So when they were strong enough to breast feed you stopped the bottle altogether for a while, did you? You didn't keep on with it a little bit all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You stopped altogether for a while?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, because ther
e wasn't sufficient in those little bottles, you know, and they didn't hold much. And you see, they would go to sleep even during the time ... That's why it took an hour to give them it, because you had to keep waking them up. Oh, what a job! But she was 
splendid, you know, and no one else ... I don't think anyone else could have had the patience to do that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In the general run of things, I mean when they weren't ill, did you husband do anything like feeding them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 'Cos he had his business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, he'd play with them a bit I should think. Mind, he took an interest in them, but no, he didn't play. He didn't understand playing with children. They never had any smaller children than he in their house, you know. I think that was, perhap
s, it. But he always wanted them ... interest them ... to take an interest. Now with Barry, he liked to have him with him in the car, and Barry was interested in the car, you see, and everything like that. And he was always happy to be with his }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 daddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , alwa
ys, except once they got lost. My husband ... not very far, but he ... they were in the country and he'd missed his usual lane, or something and he said 'oh, we're lost', or something like that, and he said 'don't you wish }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Mummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  was here? Because }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Mummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 would have known the way to go, he thought. (laughter).
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But he didn't bath them or change their nappies when they were babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, I've never known him ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But you had help so I suppose it wasn't really necessary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It wasn't necessary, no, and I was always there, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So, except for getting up and looking after them when they had whooping cough that time ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When they were ill, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It must have been quite a strain for him having to go to work as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Oh, yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Aside from that he didn't do anything else for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. Nothing else in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You remember you said with the twins you had this excellent nurse and she had to go, and then you had another one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long did that next one stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
She stayed a fortnight and then we had the one we'd engaged. But the second one, the one we had for a fortnight, she'd been nursing Jewesses, I and she was very slapdash. Oh, she was very useful to me in one way. I found I wa
sn't getting much milk when I was feeding them babies myself, and she said 'oh, you can take a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 lots more}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 than that yourself, a lot more fluid'. What was it she gave me, now? Early morning tea, a large cup or two cups. For breakfast she gave me ... what was
 it I used to drink? In the evening my big drink was Bovril, or something like that, you know, something sustaining. But other times it would be milk or ... Anyhow, palatable drinks, but I had to have lots of fluid, and I had it during the morning, and th
en after lunch and then again, afternoon and teatime, and then in the evening. Drink, drink pints. It worked the trick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was she the last nurse you had or did the original one come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, no. We'd got ... Let me see. When the original one came 
back I'd got going properly and I kept on with that 'till they didn't need it, you know, 'till I was able to wean them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long did you have ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I had that last one a month because we had to pay her, so that left me free, you know, to give the twins my attention.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
So altogether you had one nurse, or another, for about what length of time? So thinking now about that time, in your house you didn't have any relatives living with you, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Just }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Louey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 and yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did Louey have to do in the house? How long did she stay with you, by the way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, Louey was with us a year and she then went to live with her sister. But other girls I've had ... there was one we called Lizzie, she was just with us just before the last World War, but she stayed 3}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8413823  1/2}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  years, I think it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
But thinking of the ones you had before the end of the first war, what was their routine? Did they have certain jobs to do on certain days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, all the housework was done o
n certain jobs, certain days. Daily the stairs and the sweeping through and certain things, but Monday, of course, washing. Tuesday was the ironing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she do the washing and ironing all herself or was some of it sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I usually did the was
hing. Nothing was sent out. And we had a tremendous lot of washing, but I liked washing. I was in the ... Our scullery was the wash house and I was in there most of the day and the girl did most of the work and she saw ... it was cold, the midday meal, bu
t she saw to that. I didn't cook on washing day 'cos I was doing the washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And what about ironing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
The girl did the ironing. I think she did all of it, I'm not quite sure. But, you know, the girls there ... if there were jobs to be done they w
ere expected to do it in the evening. I mean ironing, or a little job like that. She had the wireless on, you know, to help her. But they weren't free. Girls were more free than most because I used to let them go off if they lived near. One girl lived nea
r and she used to go any evening when there was nothing for her to do, you see. But really, it was ... They were slaves for freedom. They didn't get any freedom. The regular one cook-housemaid, that they called cook-general, or general servant ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she have one particular evening a week she could go out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, they always had regularly one evening a week, and Sundays. But some people every other Sunday, that was only from ... the afternoon and evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not the whole Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did yours have every Sunday afternoon and evening, or an alternate one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She was supposed to have ... She had every one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she help cook Sunday dinner, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't remember about her cooking at all, at that time. Perhaps we had it cold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You didn't have a hot midday Sunday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I don't know if she helped. She helped with anything there was to do, washing up and things like that, you know, you didn't have any more done than you could possibly help. No, I can't remember, 
because I shouldn't be cooking the dinner if I went to Church in the morning, should I? I said to my husband before we were married, 'I suppose you like a hot meal on Sunday', and he said 'no, oh, no. Cold meat, we always had', which was much easier, of c
ourse. So we had hot on Saturdays.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, large joint on Saturdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you go to Church on Sunday mornings, then, after you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I don't think I went }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 too}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  much because, you see, having the babies ... I should
 do before, but we had no girl living in then. I should go more constantly always, I suppose, before Barry was born. But of course, you know, when you were near having a baby pregnant ladies didn't appear in public. Oh, no, you were not supposed to go any
where.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Really? Would you entertain in your own home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, it wouldn't matter about that, your friends would know, you see, about it, but you hid it as long as possible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Didn't you see them walking round the street and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No! Once I was taking my little grandson, Sue's brother, out one day and this was just when the children were getting used to knowing how the babies came. And we were walking along and he said, 'I think that lady's going to have a baby'. And in my d
ay they would have been shocked! Oh, fancy a child saying such a thing! (laughter) Terribly shocked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How times have changed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. We were going to buy a pram for Barry and I'd had specially made, a very nice big goat, rather smart, but big, you 
know. And I had to go on an escalator, and I didn't think anybody noticed that I was pregnant, but the man there said 'I think, Madam, you'd better take the stairs'. (laughter)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you had your mother's helps you say you don't remember them doing any cooking at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Chrissie did, because she was a cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, but that was your mother's one, wasn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, Mother's one, yes. My own, no, they didn't cook. I did the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You did all the cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I did all the cooking, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did they help, sort of preparing vegetables, and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I think I cooked ... I suppose they would have done if I'd asked them to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But it wasn't a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, no. I did the cooking.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did they do for the children, for example when Barry was little and you had the twins? What duties did they have with the children?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't ... I can't realise they had anything to do. I could leave the children with them if I wanted, but I washed them, dressed them
 and saw to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, and fed them, you see. But they would prepare anything I wanted for them, get me anything. They were your right hand, sort of, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not like a nanny, at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did they ever take them out for a walk in the afternoon or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I don't think so. Mine played in the garden. We had this big garden, you see, and until they were born Grandpa kept it. He loved gardening he hadn't much of a garden himself, and my 
husband's father and he had it lovely. Spring flowers, beautiful, everything ... But when the children got older and went to play in it he gave it up. He gave it up and they only had it for a playground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So they could play there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, they could
 play there and as I say, Barry changed the geography of the garden when he'd got some of his ideas, and the twins helped him always, you see. And I think that was what helped them to grow so big and strong. My father gave us a swing. We had the swing ere
cted at the bottom, and that swing, and climbing on walls, and all the playing they did there, it was a great help to them. I used to take them, of course, as little babies, over Primrose Hill, constantly, and along to the park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were saying that you preferred to do the things for the children yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Always, yes. I' loved it, you know. I've always loved children, and when they were my own, of course. And not ever having a career nor wanting one or anything like that ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You enjoyed doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Perfectly happy, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did you do about their clothes, and your husband's and your clothes, did you buy them or make them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, I made most of them 'till they were ... I made all the twins', when they were little, you know. We bo
ught them when they were old enough to want them. Yes, I made little trousers and everything, almost, 'till Barry was ... 'till he was a boy, you know, and have to have properly made things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did you do all the mending yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, I did them mending myself. Don't ask me how often my mending basket was emptied, there was usually some remaining for next week.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did anybody else help you with your mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The girls who worked for you didn't do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You mentioned the wife of somebody who worked in the business who was very good at all sorts of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Cleaning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, and all kinds ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, she was a carman's wife, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have her before the end of the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I only had her one day a week, that was all. Yes, it was before the end of the First World War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What sort of jobs did she do when she came round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Washing, and cleaning, mostly, but in emergency she could do anything. For Grandma Bucknell, that'd be in the earl
y days of my ... she nursed, she did anything for her. She was a very clever woman. Sewing ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did she do any sewing for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. No, I never needed that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Where did you buy the clothes? Was there a particular shop that you liked to deal wit
h when buying your children's clothes when they got a little older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, I used to go to Kentish Town to the Saxone shop, you know, the Saxone shoes. They're an American make, they were nicely fitting. Anywhere where I could get nicely fitting shoes for the children, and some of those shops are existing now, of course.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about for your own clothes? Your husband used to pay for them, didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But did he help you choose them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, he wasn't any use ... any good at that
 sort of thing (laughter). He hadn't much idea of clothes. He liked something that was brightly coloured, that caught his eye. That was all, but otherwise I wouldn't have accepted his choice. But he was quite willing for me to have what I liked, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Did you get clothes at a special season of the year? Like in your family, you said you'd got them at Whitsun, new clothes. Did you keep up that practice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, that was earlier. Very early, that was. Not in London, not after I was married. No, I g
ot clothes when I needed them. I'm not particularly ... I might say, fond of clothes. I like clothes that I think suit me, you see, and good, but if I get clothes, even now, if I'm happy and comfortable in them I'll wear them 'till they're in rags, almost
, because of the trouble of getting new, and choosing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you make any of your own when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I didn't make them when I was first married, I really hadn't time. And, besides which, it was easier to buy them. Of course, whe
n I was young and at home you didn't have ready-made clothes much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But the custom changed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I had plenty of time, and my sister ... I did the solid work, the cutting-out and the making-up and she did all the lighter jobs, the trimming and all that kind of thing, you know. And we made lots of clothes then, between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have a dressmaker, at all, when you were first married? Or did you just buy them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I had a very good dressmaker at home before I was married? A friend of mine, r
eally. She made lovely things. And she made all my wedding trousseau and everything that I brought up with me, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When the children were very small did they have any tasks to carry out regularly in the house, like you had to dust the front room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. No, they didn't have any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They didn't have any jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No. You see, they were spoilt and my husband and the boys, as I say, because we always had someone in the kitchen, someone doing the work, you see, and they were more nuisance than help. But it wasn't any training for them for when they were married.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And when Barry got to be a little bit older, when he got to be about 6 or 7 was he any help with the twins? Did he help at all ever?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, he played with them. Well, he wasn'
t old enough to do anything for them, there was only a year and 8 months between then, you see. But they always played together. Oh, yes, they were very happy together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You put them to bed yourself, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you remember if they had a certain time, you know, you liked them to be in bed by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, they went to bed at a certain time, but they didn't always go to sleep, the boys. The girls were very good. In the First World War we had Lizzie and she was ... Oh, s
he was very good with them. And we had to go into town for something, my husband and I, some shopping we had to do and we had to go to the West End. And we took the opportunity and rushed off, and as we came back the alarm had sounded and the people were 
a
ll pouring down the tube, you know, to sleep for the night. And we got to the station and my husband said, 'now, don't run'. I tried to run, but my legs felt like rubber, and he said 'now, don't run, there's plenty of time, the guns aren't near, yet,' and
 we managed to get home. And Lizzie had got them, bathed them, ... Oh, she did used to bath those twins, yes, but she was a very sweet person. She'd bathed them, and they were safely in bed by 6 o'clock, the usual time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How old were they then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It was the beginning, I should think, of that First World War. They were born in 1913.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So they must have been about 18 months, or a year, something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Or two, perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And 6 o'clock was their bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How long did they go on being in bed by 6?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, I don't know, they were pretty good at getting to bed, they were never ... You know, I think they were ready for bed, at bedtime. But the boys fought against it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did Lizzie actually put them to bed regularly, or was that just rather exceptional?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I should put them to bed if I was there, but they soon were able to do it themselves. You see, they would help each other, they didn't need so much attention, quite, as ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That's lovely, isn't it, about twins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did they share a bed, or have separate beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes. No. Let me see. They had at one time, until we cut up the room a bit more. They did share a bed, but not later. When they were quite little because, I know, they had a doll's 
pram for Christmas, and they had one between them and this doll's pram had to stand ... Yes, they must have been both in a bed then, because the doll's pram was placed at the foot of the bed, you see, Christmas. For Father Christmas to wheel it in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did they always share a bedroom, all their childhood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about Barry, was he in with them when they were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You partitioned a room off, didn't you, so that he had one half and they had the other? Oh, no, your help had one half, didn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't remember Barry. Later on Barry had that room to himself. The twins must have shared a room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were they with you and your husband for a long time when they were babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, in their ...
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In your room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, in the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I was just wondering how everybody managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. We had them in separate beds as quickly as we could, you know, but I think for a time they were in a double bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When they got to, say, 2 years old, would they have been in a room by themselves, or would they have still been with you and your husband?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no we should have moved them. We had room to have them in special rooms 'cos they were big enough. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So, would they have had one room, you and your husband another, Barry another, and your ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Little room for the living-in maid, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So you had 4 rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. They were very small, they'd cut it up so much. The room the girl had was very small, but big enough, and a large window, you k
now, she was ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She was all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How often did the children bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Once a day, only. Not morning and night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When did they have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, when it was necessary, but their clean vests and woollies, I think, 
would go weekly, unless it was necessary to clean them oftener ... to change them oftener. Yes, I don't think we changed them regularly more often, not their undies. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 
Of course, their top things had to be changed very, very often.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you eat in the kitchen or in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 dining room}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that all the meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, all the meals. But when we ... I'm just wondering. How was it we had that nice little dining table in the kitchen? I must have had a daily help then. Yes, some time I think I had to have a daily help.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 As well as the living-in one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. If I had anybody just for the morning perhaps we should feed in the kitchen, but I don't remember it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your living-in maid have her meals in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that before the rest of you, or afterwards?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I should think that she probably ate afterwards. I'm just thinking if anything had to be carved, she couldn't be ... she would be served ... But if the girl is busy bringing in the meal, and th
en there'd be the second course to bring in she wouldn't be eating. She couldn't be having it comfortably. No, she would eat afterwards, I suppose. She was always served at the same time, you see, as we were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And had the same food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you continue making bread at all, then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I couldn't do it when I came to London. I intended to but do you know, you couldn't buy the right flour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Now, Rank's Mills were in Hull, Ranks the millers and you could buy R
ank's flour but not that kind of flour, good for making bread. Some other Yorkshire friends of mine found the same, and they were very upset because they couldn't go on making their homemade bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So you gave it up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I gave it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Had it been white bread, or wholemeal bread that you made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 White.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you do anything like homemade jam and pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, I made jams and things. I do, still, as far as I can. Well, I have done up to now, homemade chutney and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was your husband also a teetotaler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, yes, he was. He'd been brought up that way, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So you didn't do any wine or beer at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, we didn't have any drinks in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you grow anything to eat at all in the way of vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, we had ... you see, these London gardens aren't much good, but during the last War my husband took up a bit of gardening. It was most unusual. We used to laugh because he had no interest at all in gardens. Wheels. Something on whe
els was all his interest. And he grew, oh, quite all sorts of things in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You wouldn't have kept any livestock, would you, in a London garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. Of course the children always had pets. No, we didn't have chickens or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your husband come home for his midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, he did. And he liked a midday meal. Preferred a midday meal to an evening one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So you had a hot dinner midday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 A hot dinner midday. And then he came in for tea because he had a lot of Cou
ncil meetings, he was nearly 20 years on the Hampstead Borough Council. And then when he came in after a ... or if he didn't have a meeting - and he did a lot of Church work, he perhaps had a Church meeting he had to go to - and if he didn't he would go b
ack to his office, catch up with some work he wanted to do there. And when he came in he just wanted a little snack, you know, of some kind, before he went to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He'd come in quite late, would he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, getting on for 11. Well, I used to go ... the last clearance of the post was 11 o'clock in London, then, and I used to go to the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 pillar box}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  - I wrote regularly to my mother and ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How often was that, that you would write to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, I think it was about twice a week, yes. And she wrote
 to me. And she'd never been much of a writer, I used to write letters for her when I was ... When I left home she started and she was a good letter-writer. And I used to go, generally it was to watch the 11 o'clock post and I used to run down the road, b
e very tired, and the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 pillar box}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 was close by my husband's office, so I would go to post my letter and call for him and we walked home over the hill, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So even when the children were very little before the War, was he working late then, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. They didn't see much of him, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, if you have your own business you do have to work very hard, don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, and he got into the habit of it, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He saw them at midday dinner, though, I suppose? When he came home for midday dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, but they weren't coming home ... when they were at school they weren't coming home for dinner. So they didn't meet, then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But when they were toddlers, though, he'd have seen them around in the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, yes, he saw them in the daytime, and had dinner at the same time as them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did you keep on the custom of having bread and milk, when you were a housewife yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Of giving them bread and milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, for breakfast, for your children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 N
o, they had ... was it porridge or cereal? They had a cereal of some kind. Not bread and milk, that was in my days, my younger days, you know, my early days. By that time they had begun to say ... the health people had begun to say that there wasn't nouri
shment in bread and milk, not enough nourishment, you know, booming the cereals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And what about a cooked breakfast, you know, fried, did they have that? Or did you and your husband have that at all in the morning?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Arthur liked a fried meal.
 Yes, we had bacon and egg sometimes, and boiled eggs, very often. I'm not particularly fond of ... I love the smell of bacon in the country, and by the sea, bacon cooking. I like the smell of it, but not much eating it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was breakfast a meal where you all sat down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, oh, no, it wasn't. The children were getting off to school, you know, and getting all ready for school, and my husband stayed in bed. He went to his office at nine o'clock and he stayed in bed 'till the last minute. He was
 such a man for sleep. And so he wasn't there when the children were busy ... Besides, it's a very unsettled time when children are busy getting off to school, you know, 'where's my so-and-so?' and 'I haven't got that ... ' (laughter). And so I thought it
 was just as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He had it in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, he wouldn't have it in bed, but he and I would have it together, you see, after they'd gone off. And the girl would get up first, you see, and she would lay the breakfast and, really, could give it to them
 if it wasn't cooked, you know. If it was an ordinary breakfast. Perhaps they would have a boiled egg with their breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She would do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did you have for tea in the evening? That was your last meal of the day, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
We didn't have a big meal. Oh, no, just a sort of bread and jam tea, you know, bread and cakes and that sort of thing. And, as I say, a little snack later, for Father. Did I have anything later? I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What sort of things would he have for a snack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, perhaps give him a little omelette, or something on toast, you know. Just a snack.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Was it different at all on Sundays? Did you have anything different for breakfast or lunch? You had this cold midday meal, didn't you, on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes. No, I don't think we had anything different for breakfast. No, I don't think so. Meals ... wasn't such a very big point with us. Food. I mean, we weren't connoisseurs of food or anything like that. I liked good, wholesome, attractive food, but 
not specially.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you say you kept the tradition of your mother's type of table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, yes. Good, nourishing food which kept the children all healthy. And he was the same, he wasn't very ... you know, not choosey about food, not saying, 'oh, I
'd like some so-and-so', or anything like that. He liked what you gave him. You see, when we were little we were all taught that it was greedy, that you shouldn't think so much about your eating, and could you have this and could you have the other, you k
n
ow. Mother always gave us that opinion that people who thought too much about food were greedy people. But yet other people say that you should take an interest, you'd find a lot of pleasure if you take more interest in your food. But we were all kept ver
y healthy and that's the main thing, isn't it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What sort of rules did you have about table manners for your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, just sort of ... particular that they shouldn't put their knives in their mouths and they shouldn't put their elbows on t
he table, and things like that, but not extreme.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You let them talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, yes. Not extreme politeness, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You let them ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, 'is there any more, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Mummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 ?' Well, if we had company they were never very stiff or exclusively polite kind of people, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Easy sort of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, if we'd had any very proper we should perhaps not have had the children there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If they didn't like something you cooked did you make them eat it, or could they just leave it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I can't imagine them disliking anything much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It didn't happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, it didn't. They weren't really particular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Could they bring a boy to the table or a book?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, I shouldn't have had things like that to interfere with ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 A meal was a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 A meal was a meal, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did they always have their same place at table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I suppose it was the place that was most convenient. When you had a high chair you'd put it where it was most out of the 
way, you see. Yes, I think they chose their own seats. The twins would always sit together, of course. Father used to sit at the head of the table, but he didn't carve. That was his seat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you serve the meal, like your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, yes, just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The servant didn't wait on you, hand round, or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, no, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When the children were young did you feel sure that there was a right way and a wrong way of bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. Yes, I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You had clear ideas about what was right?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you and your husband have the same ideas about upbringing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, yes. Oh, yes, he was quite content. I had most of the bringing-up of them, naturally, because I was with them the most
, but he was quite content for them to be brought up ... Well, we agreed, you see, we had the same attitudes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever talk about it? I don't mean argue, but just sort of discuss what you should do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I don't think we did, except as t
o when they were older and the twins were deciding what they should do, we did talk about it. Yes, we did talk about it, and their schools and that kind of thing, you see. But it was I ... I went to interview their art mistress to ask what she thought abo
ut them being interior decorators, you see. I did that. He didn't want to go with me there. He'd leave it to me in that ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was your job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And questions of who they should play with and how they should be punished, you decided that, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever have to punish them at all as they got older, or discipline them in any way at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't remember. I can't remember punishing Barry, really, but he was ... he always turned ... Yes, I can once, I remember. He
 always turned his punishments to pleasure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How did he do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
He was a tiny little boy and he started kicking. Kicking people. So I said, 'well, it's donkeys that kick, so if you behave like a donkey you'll have to be treated like a donkey', a
nd I tied him to the leg of a very heavy kitchen table we had in that old kitchen, and I went upstairs to help the girl make the beds. And we heard such a noise going on downstairs, and I came down and he was dragging this large kitchen table all round th
e
 kitchen, and he was laughing, he was having fine fun. And we had a bowl ... oh, she had peeled the potatoes, the girl, so she must have helped me with that - a bowl, a large bowl of potatoes with water over them, you know, and the bowl was going slip-slo
p with water all over, and he was so happy. And then, again, his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Daddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 had to punish him. Only once. I think men, when they do punish, they're a bit too severe, you know, I wouldn't want him to. But anyway, he climbed onto the armchair - we had a big armcha
ir in the corner near the window of the dining room downstairs, and he climbed on to the chair over the back. I don't know what he was looking at or what he was doing, and the twins - or one twin - climbed behind him and he gave her a push and pushed her 
off. And his }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Daddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 saw that and he was very angry with him. He took him in the bathroom and gave him a good spanking; shut him in, gave him a smacked bottom. Well, after a while, when we looked, streams of water were coming from under the bathroom door. He'
d turned on all the taps and he was having fun. I don't know what he was doing in the bathroom, but he was enjoying himself. I always found that. If he had to be punished he turned it into a
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Into a game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If he had to go to bed, sometimes I woul
d, say, send him to bed, you see, 'well, really, I don't mind because I'm really feeling rather tired'.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He always had an answer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your mother ever come and stay with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, whenever she could manage to stay she w
ould love to come, be with the children. Either I was there or she was up here every 2 months, and it's 200 miles which, in that time, with no cars, you know, they hadn't a car, was a great distance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You'd go up all the way with the children, did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
We went away every ... We took the children every Christmas that we could. We had to do it alternately, you know, with the other grandparents. Or they came to us. Oh, yes, the children loved to go down there at Christmas time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did you find 
that you and your mother always saw eye to eye on how you were bringing them up, or did she ever tell you that she didn't approve of your methods?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, I think so. Oh, she would tell me ... for one thing. It was rather funny; when she came up to take
 Barry back to Hull he was sitting on her bed, she was getting up ... I went in the morning into her bedroom and she was getting up, and Barry had gone to be in bed with Grandma, you see. And she got out of bed and gave him her handbag to play with, and s
h
e was just telling me, 'you know, I don't think you're particular enough about what you give this boy to play with'. And with that he started choking and we got him up to see what was the matter, and he vomited up a little bit of coloured paper, something
 he'd eaten. But Grandma looked in her bag to see if anything was missing, and she'd had a farthing and the farthing was gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He'd eaten it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, we thought he had. We thought he'd swallowed it, but you see, this was the night before the twins 
were born, I think. And nothing happened and we said 'oh, well, he can't have swallowed it'. And I said, 'well, probably ... ' - this little girl I had, you know, that was so loopy and I said -- her name was Louey, too - I said, 'perhaps Louey found it on
 the floor, you know,' so we didn't bother. But then on the Saturday, well, people always ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I was going to ask you about your mother-in-law. Did you see much of her? Did she live nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, not very near. Oh, they did at first. We're talking about the early days? Yes, they lived just round the corner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How often would you see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, very often. Yes, we often used to pop around, you know. She was very friendly. She was a sweet person. Very helpful, too. She said any time I wanted to go home and take the children, Arthur only had to go round and stay with his mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, it was lovely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did you and she have the same attitudes to child upbringing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, a great deal, except that they perhaps were
 a bit ... would be a bit more strict. I think they thought I was a bit free. If I was wanting to explain anything, explain why they should do anything she didn't think that was right. A child had to be taught to do what it was told, not question it. Only
 a few things like that, that was all the difference. But they do ... well, I think they ought to have it explained why they should do things, don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Had you been brought up that way yourself? Had your parents explained to you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4469069\charrsid8413823 why}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  they expected certain behaviour from you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, their explanation was that a thing was wrong, and you mustn't do it. You would be wicked, and a wicked person ... well! God would be displeased with a wicked person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What did you think were the most important things for a young child when you were a young mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, it's rather difficult to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Thinking in a broad way, I mean things like did you think it important to actually show children affection, to cuddle them and show them love in that sort of way, or didn't you think that that kind of affection mattered very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, it mattered to show them that you loved them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 My cuddling them and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, not too much of that, but by words and ... Yes. And by attitudes, as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about their physical safety, did you take a lot of thought about that? I mean where they played, and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I was careful about who they played with, but they never seemed to want to play with people that were ... Wel
l, they didn't play out, much, you see. And of course, the children we had in to play with them, well we were quite satisfied with. The twins had a little girl next door and she came in to play with them and they're very friendly with her still. She's mar
ried and in Devon and they still are friends. And they played with each other. There wasn't much ... other people to play with. 'Course, we'd no relatives near, no children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When they were young did you and your husband ever go out together at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Very seldom. We were nearly always in. 'Cos as I say, he had so many of his public meetings and other things he was interested in, but we did occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What sort of things would you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When I was first married, of course, we used to
 go a little to concerts. We're not terribly musical - of course, he played the Church organ for years, he could play an organ - but ballad concerts, you know, things like that. He loved organ recitals. I hated organ music, heavy organ music. I couldn't s
tand it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about dinner parties, did you go out to dinner, sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, no, no. We didn't go out to dinner parties. We weren't it that style. We would give anybody, invite them in to a nice supper, just friends, you know, but nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Informal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
When your children had a birthday, thinking now of when they were very small, you know, 5, 6, 7, do you remember what would happen, how you would celebrate a birthday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, we always had a ... I don't remember having ma
ny birthday parties. No, I didn't like birthday parties because people all came bringing presents even if they wouldn't have intended a present, you know. We had Christmas parties. But we had ... oh, perhaps just little friends, you know, not a party, but
 
always made a big celebration. One day - Barry was 4 - and we decorated the table, always, greenery out of the garden or something special in decorations, and I made him a crown of laurel leaves because he was the birthday king, and he sat at the head of 
the table, so proud being the birthday king. Always something special, you know, like that, and a treat of some kind, you know, when they got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ask other children to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes. Well, not particularly, but if they had an idea oh, I'd like so-and-so to tea', they would bring them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you do any special food or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, we always had something extra-nice, you know, for tea, some extra sweet, a birthday cake of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And on Christmas Day, did you say you'd have a party on the day, or would it be in the season?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not on the day. It was always family on Christmas Day, but during the Christmas season, yes, we had a Christmas party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How would you spend the actual day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, the actual Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, we ... of course, a lot of feeding on Christmas Day, you know, as a rule. And what did we do in between? Of course, the grownups, there was nothing much needed for them; conversation and all that sort of thing, but t
he children ... games of some kind and they generally played with the Christmas toys, you know, and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you go to Church on Christmas Day, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, we didn't. We didn't have ... We sometimes had a Christmas Day service. I 
can't remember. But of recent years at our little non-conformist church they haven't had a Christmas Day service because there are so few people, so many are away and the others, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 
housewives}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , you know, are so busy on the Christmas Day that they couldn't get ... so they have the Christmas Service on the nearest Sunday, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have any musical instruments in the home? You said your husband played the organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 My husband did, but he played the piano. He didn't play the piano well, but he
 did play the organ, but we always had a piano in the house. I could play so far, but not very far.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about the children, did they have lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, they had lessons, but really, they didn't seem to show much aptitude at all and in the end 
they gave it up, but I think, now, if they'd had better teaching ... We sent them to the best teacher there was in the neighbourhood. She could get her pupils through the early exams, but she didn't teach them in any interesting way at all. And at the sam
e
 time I went to tea with a friend that I'd made and her little boy had just been sent to the London College of Music and he'd been taught in quite a different fashion. Instead of going through all the he was set to make himself a little tune on the piano,
 you know, to get him used to it. Do you know, his name was Tony Hopkins and I think it's that Anthony Hopkins from ... that you hear. I've often felt inclined to write and say how I remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4469069\charrsid8413823 
go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 ing to tea with his mother. But she died immediately after that, the mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you sing at all when you had your own family? Did you sing songs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, we didn't have sing-songs. Barry ... oh, he was grown up. We haven't got to the grown-up stage yet. But when he was smaller, I used to sing in my youn
ger days, contralto songs, and he didn't like the type of song. There were two. You know, we used to sing too sad songs and things like that, you know. There was one song that was popular, Oh, Dry Those Tears, Life Was Never Made For Sorrow, sort of senti
mental songs, you know, and he didn't like them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I didn't ask you, I think, whether your husband saved up any money before getting married, or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Myself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, you or your husband, whether you had any sort of savings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, he had enough money to furnish a house. Let me see. He spend }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13117750 \'a3}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 150 on the furnishings, which was quite good. He'd saved it, but I don't know where.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But he did save some money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But I suppose you didn't because you'd been at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I didn't, I've never saved money, ever.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you get any help from your parents in setting up the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, only ... You see the bride, always in those days, provide all the bed-linen and the household linen and things like 
that. Father supplied all that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Which was quite an expense?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, yes. It was quite an expense, in those days. The hand work, the work that we put into it. We embroidered sheets and pillowcases and all sorts of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your husband get any help from his parents? Any particular help for setting up his home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, except a good wedding present. Grandpa gave us the bedroom suite. It was very nice. It was an old one that he'd bought at a sale and it was very, very nice, sort of period ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I didn't ask you whether you enjoyed breast-feeding the babies. Did you actually enjoy it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was there anything at all in the house that your husband did, like decorating, painting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not himself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Presumably you had men in to do that if you wanted it done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, we'd men in to do anything. The least little thing I'd send somebody round and he had it done, to his liking, of course. And he was ... he'd very good ideas in the decorating.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did he do anything at all himself in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Nothing? It wasn't necessary, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, not a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And anything at all in the way of domestic ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He would tinker about with electrical things, rather. As they were running an ele
ctrical department he thought, just before Barry was born and pregnant ladies didn't go out, you know, not to be seen, so he thought a good idea would be for him to be taking electrical classes, and so he got an electrical wiring certificate, just so that
 he had some knowledge, because they were running an electrical business, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would he do that in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. He used to tinker about and make gadgets sometimes, but we used to say they were a kind of Heath Robinson affairs. They alwa
ys worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did he know how to cook? Could he have cooked if he'd had to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, not the slightest idea. He boasted he could boil an egg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever have to go short of anything at a meal so that your husband and children could have more?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, we never had any shortage of ... I mean, if it was something they liked particularly I ... Food had never been terribly important to me, I mean, I shouldn't have minded giving them the larger share, of course, but we were never short, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your husband have bigger helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. He was satisfied. He hadn't a terribly big appetite, but he enjoyed his food and everything, he didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you let the children, when they were little, join in grown 'ups' conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, they wouldn't have done that. They wouldn't want to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If you had a friend in, would they be in the room with you? If a friend came round to call?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, but I didn't have ... Well, they would be at school in the afternoon, wouldn't they, and I 
didn't have many friends in the evening. We didn't have much social life, you see, Father was always busy with his meetings, his Council meetings, and he would go back to the office if there was work he wanted to finish, you know, that kind of thing, so t
hat that kind of social life we didn't have, much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you ever remember them joining in or interrupting a conversation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't remember it happening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. No, I don't think so. I had a niece in one day and we were talking, an
d Barry was quite tiny. And we'd been to the seaside and he'd had a donkey - he was 17 months old and he had a ride on a donkey and the donkey was called Billy, so always donkeys were Billy Donks after that. And so we bought him a little donkey and he was
 
sitting ... I was talking to my niece and I heard him say - he couldn't pronounce esses - and he said 'Lit on Billy Donk, big man', and we turned round and there he was ... they wore tunics, little boys of that age, and there he was with ... you couldn't 
s
ee anything of Billy Donk at all, but he'd managed to balance his little fat self on this tiny donkey, and say 'big man'. So that's only the sort of interruptions I ever had. Oh, no, they weren't so clinging, they were self-sufficient. And, of course, the
 twins had each other, and Barry always had some occupation, something he was keen on doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
If you and your husband wanted to talk about something which you didn't want the children to hear would you do it, then, when they weren't around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, yes. Never talked about private things ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 People do it nowadays, a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, they do. Margaret lets her little boy, the adopted little boy, she lets him break into conversations and ask what the people are talking about, and that kind of thing. I wouldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you say that the ideas they had about how to behave they got more from you, or more from their father?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, more from me, yes. They had more time with me, and more notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And what were the things that you particularly wanted them to grow up thinking important in life? Important values?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, particularly honesty, truthfulness and ... well, all the real things that matter. That I think matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you ever remember them having any worries, being wo
rried about anything and them telling you about it? When they were small, I mean, 6 or 7.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, I don't think so. As I say, they asked questions like they all do. Little David, the youngest one, he was in his bath one night, just lying enjoying the war
m water and he said 'Mother ... ' - they always called me Mother, I taught them to call me Mother. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Mummy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 hadn't come in much at that time; it was Mama and Dadda, and I much preferred Mother. He said, 'Mother, why should I have to do what you tell me?' He w
anted to know where the authority came from. Well, that was difficult, but, as I told you before the big, the highest authority was God, of course, and I said to him, 'Well, first I'm the one that God sent you to, to be looked after until you're a man, un
t
il you're old enough to look after yourself, and if I didn't tell you what was right to do, then I should be not doing my ... what I was told to do, or my duty', you know, and I said 'And then again, if children don't do what their parents tell them, well
, they have to go to the judge and he has to tell them what to do'. We was quite impressed, but I don't know that he was any more obedient.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How did you want them to behave towards you, in particular, can you remember? What sort of behaviour you and you
r husband expected of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I can't. They were always loving, they were never rude to us or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You didn't have a struggle exacting certain kinds of behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, not at all. We didn't ask any particular behaviour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I meant the general way. As you said, they weren't rude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, oh, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you have liked them to feel that they could come and tell you about their worries, if they did have worries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes. Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you play any games with them at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, they played together, they didn't want me. Oh, we played ... would that be up to the First War when he played ping pong? We had a ping pong table we put on, you know and I played with Barry as a reward for getting his homework done. 
I play with him. And then I ... he could beat me, and then I took on the girls. I took them on one after the other, you know, until the last one could beat me, and then I gave up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about games like Snap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, we had those sort of games, 
played with them if they wanted to. We didn't have playing cards, I've never played, I haven't much ... oh, I haven't much brain, I think, for Bridge or anything like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did you have things like Snakes and Ladders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, Snakes and Ladders and all those kind of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you play them with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Happy Families. Yes, if they wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about games outdoors? Do you ever remember when they were little playing outside with them with a ball, or your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, yes, he would play with a ball and play cricket with them sometimes, but they played in the garden, mostly, you see, and in London here we had a good-sized garden. Did I show you the picture of my mother with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, that garden, y
ou'll notice, it's neglected entirely it used to be beautiful before the children were ... then it was given over to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When they were little did you read aloud to them ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I can't remember, but I suppose so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't remember that? Or your husband reading to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, Father never had the time, and that was my business, looking after the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you belong to a library at all when they were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't think there was 
a children's library at that time, they've been developed later. A newspaper? Yes, my husband had a newspaper, took a newspaper. I forget which one it was. It would be a conservative type one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have books in the house, much? That the children could read if they wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, we didn't have ... They had their own young toy books, you know and that kind of thing, but we weren't great readers. I loved reading, but I didn't really ... I was spoilt with my reading because, as I told you, we li
ved where we had that great big newsroom and when it was bedtime and I used to slip away, and I used to read all these magazine types, you know. But I intended doing some serious reading later on and I went to some classes, art classes, and if you took a 
f
irst certificate for drawing you had a 5/- prize. And a five shilling book, then, you could get a leather bound copy and I chose all kinds of books. A Ruskin, I had, and Spencer's Fairie Queen, and all kinds of things. I never really properly read them, y
ou know. Oh, later on, later on I would. I was too ... many things I was enjoying. When I was 56 my children would be grown up and I would start my re-education. The time hasn't come yet, I've been far too busy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever go away for a holiday when the children were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, we started when I was 7.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I mean your children were little.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, when my children were little, yes. You see, there was the War and they were ... What age would they be, now? I think the little ones would be about 5 and 6.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 About 5 and 7?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
About 5 and 7. Perhaps a little bit older, because Barry ... Oh, no, at that time we went to Broadstairs, that was the first holiday we had. We took a house there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that before the end of the First War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, after, just immediately after, and we had ... I don't know whether we had a fortnight or a month there, I can't remember. But after that we did used to stay ... have a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was your first family holiday, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, because it was ... you know, the first we could after the War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Do you ever remember the children, when they were little, going out with just their father? Taking one, or two or 3 of them out on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, he would take them, but not formally take the
m out properly. He took them to the Church one day, a little Church near, because we had this little cottage. Did I tell you? We had this little cottage in the War. My cousin had the offer of this from a farmer. She lived in Radlett but she'd always wante
d
 a little really rustic cottage, you see, and she found she could have this one for 3 shillings a week and she came to us and said would we like to share, take the children out of London, you see. And of course, we did. Eighteen pence a week. (laughter) B
u
t that was lovely there. And one Sunday he offered to take them to Church, to the little Church there and they went and all got settled in the Church. And before long, one of them 'must go outside', she must go outside, the tinker! And the whole lot had t
o stream out! (laughter) I don't think he took them any more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How much time did you spend down there in the cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, quite a lot. But you see, we had all our rations and everything in London. You couldn't have a coal ration anywhere else, nor
 a food rations and so that made it very awkward. Oh, I did work hard in that War.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How did you manage, then, about your rations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I had to come up to London and get them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How frequently was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And we ... Once a week I came up for th
e rations and I came ... I had a little girl, then, that I could leave in charge of the children. She was not very old but she was very good and I used to come up at about ... I think I left home about half past 6 to 7 and ... I had a bicycle, but I can r
e
member walking many a time a mile and a half to the station. Then I got to London ... Which station would it be? I can't remember where we arrived. Finchley Road or Kentish Town. It was on that line. And I came and opened the office because that was the n
i
ght when Father was doing his volunteer driving, you see, driving the soldiers. And I opened and stayed there 'till 11. And I was also trying to pick up a bit more book keeping in cases he was ... in case he had to go. Then he came and took over the offic
e
 and I went for the rations because our people we were registered with were all near there, you know. Went back to King Henry's Road and cooked a joint - well, as big as we could get, it wasn't very much - and cooked that and the old Grandpa would come in
 
and have his meal with us so he didn't have to go home that day. And tidied up the house a bit and was ready ... We hadn't much cooking apparatus, only a Primus stove at the cottage and so we couldn't cook a joint or anything. And then we were both ready 
t
o go back to catch a train, I think, about 8 o'clock. And my husband wouldn't be home long because he had to leave early in the morning, you see. And one night when we got there we'd missed the train and I said, 'now you mustn't come back because it isn't
 
worth it', and he was tired, and I said 'I'm quite all right I can go home alone'. He said, 'well, you'll have your bicycle at the station, won't you', and I said 'yes', but I knew I'd told my sister - she was staying with us, her husband was in the Army 
a
nd she'd brought her children to stay with us - and I knew I'd told her that if she was home first she could take that bicycle, you see, to ride home. And so when I got there and got out of the train the guns were going over London. I'd left my husband th
e
re to sleep and I was worried. But, you know, it wasn't so bad in that time, but we thought it was very bad, you know, the zeppelins coming over, mostly. And so ... 'Well, I thought, 'there's nothing for it. I must walk'. And I'd got the rations, they wer
e
n't very much, but I had them in a knapsack. And my cousin was out, as I passed there, she was out watching the guns over London. And she said 'where's Arthur?' 'Oh,' I said, 'I've left him behind because of ... ' 'Well, she said, 'Ruby's taken your bicyc
l
e'. Ruby had seen her on the way. 'Oh', she said, 'get on, then. Get on'. Well, we had to go down these lonely country roads and it was hay-making time. I thought if I met a tramp I'd got these rations, I'd got this kitbag round my hand if I should meet a
n
ything. If a cow had mooed at me over a gate! Well, the tress met in some places, you know. A mile and a half to go! However, I got there safely. Rub said, 'you've never walked up here by yourself!' Well, I had to. There was nothing for it. And I used to 
... as I say, had to mend their shoes. Women were supposed to do the men's jobs in that War.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 How did you learn to mend their shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I don't know. I hadn't had any proper training, but I looked at those that had been done and ... Oh, I got 
to do it quite professionally in the end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Before that they'd been mended at a shoemakers, presumably, your husband hadn't done them, had he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no. No, he'd never done anything. Oh, he did used to ... he was very good at putting on rubber soles
 and rubber heels and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did he do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, he used to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did you grow things? Did you grow vegetables and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, no. Oh, no, you couldn't do anything like that. We could buy things, I think, there.
 There was a shop in the town. You couldn't buy your ration things but otherwise there was a shop we could walk into Radlett. And we used to go into St. Albans. That wasn't too far away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But your husband used to be most of the time in London, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And how many years did you stay there in the cottage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
We had to give it up when the ploughman came back after the War. Immediately after the War, we had to give it up. But it was lovely. It was lovely for the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were you there through most of the War? Three or 4 years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, we should be, yes. I remember once, the children had had very bad chicken pox and we were taking them there, really to get over it. And Father was kept at the office. We intended starting quite ea
rly - it was Easter time and very cold, in fact it snowed while we were there. We wanted to start quite early, he was kept late and it was quite late when we started off, and when we got half-way there I found we'd left some rugs behind. But my cousin was
 
in charge of this cottage and she said she would see that it was aired and ready for us. But when I got there I found that she hadn't been able to go and she had a little help, she was only quite a young girl, and she'd sent her to see to this airing of t
he cottage, and I wasn't happy about it at all. It seemed damp for me. They sat up until every single thing had been aired before the fire we managed to have there, so far. And they didn't hurt. They got over it. They got over it beautifully.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When did you see your husband, then? Did he come down at weekends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I think he came down most ... I think he came down most days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 After work, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And he'd have to get off pretty early in the ...?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Get off very early in the morning, yes. And he came up, also, on Sundays to play the organ at the Church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Up to London, you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes. One Sunday, I remember, he'd come up and we had no coal for the fire and there was no wood round about there that you could gather, or anything, but we'd got lots of paper and stuff and so ... }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Daddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  used to turn the corner. We could see him turn the corner to come home, and I said, 'now watch out and when you see }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Daddy}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  turning the corner, we'll put on all this paper that we've got and we'
ll have a blaze when he comes in'. And we did. We had a blaze when he came in. Oh, it was all fun, all those sort of things, you know. They never minded hardships.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did the children start school there? Did Barry go to school there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. We must have only been there in the holidays. I don't remember. The little ones weren't at school, not the twins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did Barry go to school in London? During the War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 We can't have been at the cottage all the times ... Walked with them in the pram, I think, 
into Queen's Crescent. You don't know that, do you? It's Kentish Town way, to get some dates. I heard that in Queen's Crescent you could buy a lb, of dates. Couldn't get those sort of things, so I took them over and we got the dates. Of course, they had a
bout one }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4469069\charrsid8413823 each,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 the rest was ... I was going to make a date pudding for them. And then we got them up, the zeppelins were over, and no light, of course, and we got them all settled nicely, and ... 'And now bring out the dates'. So of course, I had to bring o
ut the dates and give them some. A special treat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were saying how your husband would play the organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that regularly that he did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, he played the organ for many years. As a boy he used to be the organ blower, but 
then we got ... changed it to ... it didn't have a blower.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What denomination?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It's a Baptist Church, that they went to, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did you start going to that, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I belonged ... Yes, I was a member of a congregational church in Hull a
nd they're very much the same, you know, only they have adults baptism at the Baptist if you wish. We're not the strict ones. People can be members without, so I was just transferred. My membership was transferred from the Congregational to this Church wh
ere he belonged.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Can you tell me whether you went occasionally to Church, or fairly regularly
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, regularly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Every Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did he or you belong to the choir there? at any time up to the end of the War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I was never in the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And he couldn't have been if he was playing the organ, could he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was there a temperance club there, at the Baptist Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't think so. It was in my early days when you had the Band of Hope, they were called. No, there was no special temperance clubs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were there any clubs or activities to do with the Baptist Church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 They had a Boy's Brigade, which was very good. Boys up into their 'teens went there, and a Girls' }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4469069\charrsid8413823 Brigade.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  And then recently, not so long ago, 
they've had ... gathered together, you know, They've had reunions, and it's surprising how well they'd all done, those boys and those girls who belonged there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about clubs or anything for adults, would they have anything for them? There wouldn't be any women's groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
They had a women's meeting in the afternoon, but only a few ... They used to be young married women and they had a little - at one time - just a little cr\'e8che in a side room to mind the babies whilst they had their meeting.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you belong to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. But afterwards, you see, all the women go out to work. It's no good having anything afternoons for young women, now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But at that time you didn't go to the meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I was too busy with my babies at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you have liked the idea of putting them in a cr\'e8che while you went to a meeting of mothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I never thought of it, really. There'd never been any need.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about Sunday School? Did the twins and Barry go to Sunday School?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, they went to Sunday School. I asked them later on why they went: 'Did you like it?' 'Oh, no,' they said, not particularly, they didn't dislike it, 'Oh, no', they said. 'Why did you go, then?' and they said, 'Well, we suppose we felt it was our duty t
o go'. And David, the youngest one, he wouldn't go. He didn't like Sunday School, but we never let him go, we never bothered about it. Well, as a matter of fact, when he was killed he was secretary to ... There were some young men in Hampstead who were ru
nning what they called a Drawing room Class, Drawing room Bible Class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did they go to any family services? Did they go to any other services?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When they were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 There weren't services for little children to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, only the Sunday School. And then older on, the Brigades, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And what about Sunday? How did you keep Sunday in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, we were not so old-fashioned as not to go out Sundays, but we didn't go during service time. But i
mmediately after they came from Sunday School we were out to the car and away we went to the country.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you play games with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you have allowed them to play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, Father would, but they weren't ... game
s were not played in public places at that time. But the cinemas wanted to open on Sunday and they brought round a ... what do you call it, for everybody to sign ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 A petition?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Petition for everybody to sign against this. And I thought, now wha
t are these young people to do? All around our neighbourhood they had about a couple of rooms, they couldn't take their young friends in, you see, they'd only have to hang around the streets or something. And I thought, well unless we could do something t
o
 avoid that I'd no right to sign that petition and I didn't. And I don't think I did sing it. But we started, my husband and I having an evening after Church ... having ... 8 'till 10 o'clock, having a little sort of singsong, or anything. You'd get down 
a
 good speaker, a little social evening. First we had it at the Church and then some peoples thought it wasn't quite right to have all community singing and that kind of thing in the Church, so we transferred it to our house. We did that for 3 years and th
e
n I think it was the War broke out. Anyhow, he was very active in that, my husband, because he was very good at getting speakers. He was very friendly and people were friendly with him, you know, and he got all sorts of people to come and speak to that Su
nday evening. He got a bank manager, somebody he knew. He got ... Oh, no, that was for a Friday meeting we had later on, and they called it The Friday Forum, and that was very good. He got one of the lady }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Mayoresses}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , I think, that we had, and he got ... oh, different ... He got the sweep who lived }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 
next-door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  to tell his experiences, and all kinds of different people. It was very good.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was the Friday Forum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that after the War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 That was after, yes. But these young people, you know, they remember. When I meet them again they remember those Sunday evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It must have been nice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you have family prayers ever in your own family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, we didn't. I thought afterwards we really ought to have d
one, but I don't know. But our times were so irregular, you know, and ... Well, I don't think we were really as devout as we might have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you say Grace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, we said Grace, as a rule, and particularly on Sundays. Not always because Fathe
r wasn't there sometimes and meals were a bit irregular, you see, like that. But we did always on Sundays. And we had the person to dinner one Sunday - we used to, you know, with these young }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4469069\charrsid8413823 
persons,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  when we had some visiting ones, we used to entertain the
m at our house - and I said, 'say Grace, Barry, and Barry said, 'I don't know it', as if we were just putting it on for show to the person. He meant he'd forgotten it, I think, but to let you down like that!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you did say it, would it be at all meals? Or would it be at one particular meal where you would normally have said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, just one particular meal. The midday meal. Yes, and particularly Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Were the children taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, from being little. Afterwards we left it to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that you or your husband who taught them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I taught them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You mentioned that your husband would have taken a conservative paper; were his views conservative in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, they were. He was a member of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 Hampstead}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  Borough Council for nearly 20 years, on the Conservative side, you know, because they did have party sides even then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Do you have any idea why he held Conservative views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you discuss politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I wasn't in
terested, no. I don't know much about politics. I ... Even now I can see so much good in each promise that I find it hard to decide which is the best to vote for. I should vote for the man whose character I thought was the best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 What about when you ha
d your first vote? Do you remember when that was? Would it have been 1919? That was the first time women had the vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 1919, was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, well, it was practically ... I was married in 1910, I should have it 9 years. I don
't remember women getting the vote. Didn't they have it before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, that was the first election when they had the vote. You don't remember the first time you voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It wasn't an event to me. I remember the suffragettes, and they were ... al
l that we knew about them was those awful women, so unfeminine!! And so, oh, terrible!!
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did both your parents feel that way about them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I don't think Father expressed an opinion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But your mother didn't like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He wouldn't say ... No, Mother didn't like them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In your views on politics when you were a young married woman were you Conservative in your views, or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I was not particular on any side, really. And we never told each other how we voted, thought. I took a little more interest later on.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. It was secret and so we left it so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You don't remember the first time you voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Which way you voted?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was your husband actually a member of the Conservative Party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes. Yes, he was. He was ... When he retired from the Conservative Party, I forget what office he had there. He was a member, anyhow, and they wrote and thanked him for his support, you know, all that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did he work for them at a general election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, he ran around with his car taking people and all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you do anything at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not for any party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would he have liked you to, do you think, or did he leave that quite to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I think perhaps he might have liked me to, now I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But he didn't urge you to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, no, not at all, but I think I might have shown a bit, now. Ought to have shown a bit more interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You just weren't interested?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I was inte
rested in what they were doing, but I couldn't ... I didn't know sufficient about the policies of each party, you see, to feel ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 To feel that one was better than another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. I felt it's really not for me, I'm not able to be a help to any side.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And during times that weren't general election times he was active in being on the Council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was he on the Council before the end of the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4469069\charrsid8413823 F}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 irst War? Or was it later that he got on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, he was on the Council 'till not long befor
e he died. He was certainly on the Council - he retired because of his health ... let me see, he died in '56 and he was ill 3 years. He was on 'till about ... we came here in '54, he was still on then. He was on 'till a year, I think, before he died, so .
..
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 He would have got on in the 1930's, then, would he? For the first time, do you think? In the 1920's or 1930's.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 If that was nearly ... He was on 18 years. Yes, well that'd ... you reckon it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was he a member of any clubs or institutes or organizations?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Only the Conservative Council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, wait a minute. He was on committees. He was on the committee for re-employment, something to do with ... in connection with business. He was on a lot of committees.
 He was on a committee for the S.O.S., a branch of the S.O.S. Society. That was for down and outs, you know, and one of their hostels was quite near to my husband's office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was that in later years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, in later years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And in the earlier years was he on anything then, any committees, or did these interests come later, on the whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, he was always interested in things generally. I don't remember him having office, being on committee when we were married. No, it was later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 N
ow you had these 3 very young children most of the time that we're talking about, but was there anything outside the home that you had time for, that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, I gave my time entirely ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were fully occupied with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, I was, with the children, you see. It was only by extreme care that we kept the twins alive and there was no time for anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It was really wonderful that they survived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I've always felt that my ... it was my most important thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You said that in the early days you'd sometimes go out together to a concert
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, we used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was there anything else you'd go and do together? In your free time, or in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, just odd things, I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did you ever go to the cinema or the theatre?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
We went to the theatre occasionally, but that was generally, not because I hadn't other things that were quite as important to me, but we had a lot of visitors, you see. During the first 18 months bef
ore Barry was born I had 50 people from Hull visiting me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And all staying the night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Some just for the day, but not all staying, but many of my friends staying a week or a fortnight, or so, and so we were very busy. Well, you see, London's such a center.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
I was going to ask you about your relationships with neighbours. Did you have any neighbours that you were friendly with or Co-operated with?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 In London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, in London.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No. That was what ... the difference there is, you know, in London. Now, there were some people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 next-door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 ... we lived there, oh, for many years, How long had we lived there? The children were just growing up ... and they were very nice people, but we thought they didn't care for children. They didn't seem to
 take much notice ... any notice of them, and we never knew them, but we found out later that they were such nice people and they did, you know, they did like children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Why did you think that they didn't?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Because they never took any notice, you 
see, they were just ... the sort of people that you must be introduced to, to take notice of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did they live }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 next-door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, but then ... Then there were some people that had a flat }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 next-door}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , later, and they had one little girl and she was a friend with our children and she came and played in our garden. And she's still their friend; she's living down in Devon now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I think that's the one your daughter mentioned, as being close to both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But did you have any neighbours sort of dropping in for a cup of tea, and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, only ... My cousin lived for a time a few doors down the road from us and they were often in and out. They popped in and out, you see. But otherwise you wouldn't have had ... And
 do you know, during the War I got to know some of the neighbours round about, they were bombed when we were, and found they were awfully nice people. There was a woman next door, she was obviously died hair and used to wear very bright clothing, you know
, and we used to call her 'that common-looking woman }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 next-door}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
'. And when she was bombed we were in the same ward, and I found out she'd married a chef. He was killed ...
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You were saying that a lot of people, when you were asked to sign this petition, 
a lot of people you said were living in a couple of rooms. Were those people poorer people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, they would be. They were just working people, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Nearby you, was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, nearby in the neighbourhood round us. It's a neighbourhood 
that had been rather exclusive, you know and had gone down and down, and now it's going up and up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It's interesting, isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, it is. They're making flats and the houses that are being sold, for a tremendous price. The value has gone up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Those poorer people, the working people, did you see much of how they lived? When you were a young wife, at first? Had you had anything to do with them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not until - unless it was people who worked for us, but not until later on when I had the cla
ss in the Sunday School and knew the girls there, you see. I knew them all then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 But Barry went to the Council school, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, he went to the Council school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 You didn't meet other parents when you went to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I met one wo
man who later came to our Church. I knew her there. I admired her so much. I don't know whether she was a widow or whether her husband had a very poor job, but oh, I did admire the way she managed those children. When they had to be undressed for the doct
or I could see how she'd made their little underclothes from larger garments, you know, and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 She had very little money, did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, yes. Very little money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Would you say, among the working class people round you was there 
a wide variation in the living standard of different families? Were some much poorer than others, do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, I didn't know them intimately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not enough to say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Not enough to say, no. I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you lived, round King Henry'
s Road, who would you say were the most important people? Were there any people who were sort of generally well known?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, a lot of people in King Henry's Road were well known people. Marie }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 
Lloyd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , the music hall person, lived up there at one time. An
d there were the ... oh, what did they call them? Some very good musical people. And then came into King Henry's Road from Germany well known - who came over? One of the big philosophers? Tell me some of the big names.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, there was that one who was on the Brains Trust, J}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4469069\charrsid8413823 oad.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Oh, no, this was a German, and he didn't speak English as a matter of fact, but he was a writer, but he was a well known name. How silly of me! But he couldn't speak English and we, in our flat, we had a young couple at th
e top flat who had escaped from Germany. She was a medical student, I don't know if she was fully qualified, and he was law, and they'd escaped. They were very poor. And someone came from this ... it begins with an E. oh, dear, I'm so sorry. My memory is 
gone. And this doctor girl, she was going to give him English lessons and she was suddenly rushed off to hospital with a terrible sudden illness, it was a conception in the ovary tube. Have you heard of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The Fallopian tube?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The Fallopian tubes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, my mother had one of these. Terrible thing, very dangerous, too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, very terrible. Well, they came with a message from him to her about these lessons and the person who came could only speak German.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When did he come over? Was that before the second World War?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 The house you had in King Henry's Road, did you own it or did you rent it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, it was owned. I don't know whether it was owned, like, by the company, they usually used to if there was any property it w
as generally the company, which was Grandpa and Father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And when you were living there, when you were first married you had all these friends coming from Hull, did you also have local friends?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Well, mostly the Church friends, you know. No, I had
n't many personal friends. I had relatives, in London. Quite a number of relatives, you see, and they came in and out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Did your husband have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Mostly relatives. You see, if you make friends at school or anywhere like that ... He made a fr
iend at the evening electrical classes that I told you he went to, he made a friend there, but they get separated, you know, and they can't keep up with the friendship so much as you can in the provinces.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 So when people came to see you it was mostly relatives, was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, mostly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Do you remember any particular friend - I mean, the one he made at the evening institute, would he come round and have meals with you at all, or tea, or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, yes, I'd have asked him in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Was he a single man, or did he have a wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
No, he was single, and ... Oh, another thing Father went in for. He thought he would like to be a surveyor. Yes. And he took the ... was it a surveyor? Yes. He took the classes and he got near the exams, 
and this other young man with him - he was taking the same exam - and then Arthur found out that he couldn't be ... he had not to be connected with a building firm or any firm in that line before ... you know, whilst he was taking this exam. If he'd known
 
that he would have, well, stood down. Let his Father do the ... nominally take over, or something like that, you know, for 3 months so that he could have got it. He was terribly disappointed. And this other young man passed the exams, but I think he died.
 
I think he died, yes. And his youngest friend that he had, his boyhood friend, he went out to Canada and he joined the Canadian Princess Patricia's Company, it was called, Princess Pat's ... and he was killed. So he hadn't any particular friends except th
e manager of his electrical department who was his friend before he came, he got him in to manage that department and he did 'till he's just retired at about 80.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 When you were young and first married, did he have a wife, the manager of the electrical department?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 No, he married just after we did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And were you friendly with her, too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, we were friendly, but we didn't visit much, you know. We were Church friends and friendly in everything, but didn't do much visiting. His wife was a ve
ry active woman with the Church work she did marvelous work there, and ... well, they were very sociable and were very nice, but I don't know, we didn't seem to feel it was necessary to invite you to a meal and all that kind of thing, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 It was more relatives that you did that with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Who were your relatives that were living in London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Well, my aunt, she came to London ... All their families, except my mother, they had to go out to do some work, you know, and there was no work for people at that time except domestic or be a governess. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 And she was a nanny to some people in Hull, very, very well-known people in Hull - in fact they gave a park, there's a park named after them - and she was their nanny and she came to London with them. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
They had a London house and I think they left Hull and came to London and she came up with them and she met her husband there and married, and stayed in London. And, of course, that was how I came up to London, to stay with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Oh, that was the one? I remember you telling me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 And did she have children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
Yes, and it was her daughter that used to live down the road. Yes, we ... oh, we did quite a bit of visiting, you see, amongst us. And she had one little girl - she had
 a baby that died, but she'd one little girl and the little girl was very fond our out children, so of course, she was in and out as much as she could. And she tells me all the things that they used to do that I'd forgotten. She says Barry, he was so engr
ossed in what he was doing that he never could get up to the lavatory in time, he used to wet his knickers. His little wool}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
en knickers used to be nearly always wet. The lavatory was upstairs, and she said she met him going up one day on all fours, he was s
o small he was crawling, and he was saying to himself, 'oh, he was a good boy, he was a good boy', to himself (laughter). I tell him now if there's anything ... he isn't a bit conceited about anything he does, but if there's any sign that he's done anythi
ng good, 'say to him, 'he was a good boy', and he remembers. But that's really not to the point.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15536214 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 I think I've covered all the points, actually.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15891618 DB  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 Yes. How lucky it was to me that those people were all nice people. There was nobody rough or - or - 
well what we used to say common, you know, crude sort of people. They were varied, all of them but - they were all - although they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 shop keeping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 , but they seemed rather superior to - there was no - as I say, rough or - people. They weren't particularly
 that well educated you know, most of them. Although there were two - three little ladies of the - in the end shop, the Miss Burets, they ran a - a - a little cake shop and - oh sweets and that sort of thing, what do you call it, confectionery, all their 
o
wn making, and oh they were sweet little old ladies. Quite ladies you know. The Miss Burets, anything from there was lovely. They were very nice. Then there was a - another little single lady that had a baby linen and small bakery shop. She was a very nic
e person. There was a chemist at the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 comer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
, I didn't know him. And - then there was a tiny shop with - a tobacconist, but they were nice people, they were next door to us on the other side. Here very nice people. And then there was the plumber that - had fo
ur sons and - well, we didn't care very much for he was rather a - proud sort of man but the boys were nice. One of them I used to play with and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 then came}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  back and he was a person. And - over the fish shop, there was a young man, his name was Harold Hodgso
n and Mrs Hodgson, we were rather doubtful whether she was Mrs but she was called Mrs, she was a very superior kind of person who was very ladylike and very - and yet smelled of fish, with living in the fish shop. Yes. Oh yes, all together - but I mean we
 
all - a nice - really a nice class of people. There was grocer there and - he was a young man, with a family and his wife was very nice and - and - quite nice type of people you know, all - all fairly refined types. Whether that was because - that was gen
eral with the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 shop keeping}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823 
 class or whether it was because we'd come out of the town into the new neighbourhood where there was nice people around you see, I don't know. You know, they were just building these streets around at the back of us and they - I t
hink I told you, they were filled with - white collared people with good positions. Some of them actually earned two pounds ten a week. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11632573\charrsid8413823 It}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11825398\charrsid8413823  was a lot. Yes, I had a friend who married - she married a cousin who was a widower in London, he was in a bank and - three pounds a week his - amounted to. Yes.
